  string
  line 2
  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `12A. Power of Chief Commissioner or Commissioner and of Joint Commissioner to make enquiries`
  line `under this Act.`
  line `CHAPTER IV`
  line `A SSESSMENT`
  line `13. Return of gifts.`
  line `14. Return after due date and amendment of return.`
  line `14A. Return by whom to be signed.`
  line `14B. Self-assessment.`
  line `15. Assessment.`
  line `16. Gift escaping assessment.`
  line `16A. Time limit for completion of assessment and re-assessment.`
  line `16B. Interest for defaults in furnishing return of gifts.`
  line `17. Penalty for failure to furnish returns, to comply with notices and concealment of gifts, etc.`
  line `17A. Penalty for failure to answer questions, sign statements, furnish information, allow inspections,`
  line etc.
  line `18. Rebate on advance payments.`
  line `18A. Credit for stamp duty paid on instrument of gift.`
  line `CHAPTER V`
  line `L IABILITY TO ASSESSMENT IN SPECIAL CASES`
  line `19. Tax of deceased person payable by legal representative.`
  line `19A. Assessment of persons leaving India.`
  line `20. Assessment after partition of a Hindu undivided family.`
  line `21. Liability in case of discontinued firm or association of persons.`
  line `21A. Assessment of donee when the donor cannot be found.`
  line `CHAPTER VI`
  line `A PPEALS, REVISIONS AND REFERENCES`
  line `22. Appeal to the Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) from orders of Assessing Officer.`
  line `22A. [ Omitted.].`
  line `23. Appeal to the Appellate Tribunal.`
  line `24. Powers of Commissioner to revise orders of subordinate authorities.`
