  string
  line 3
  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `25. Appeal to the Appellate Tribunal from orders of enhancement by Chief Commissioner or`
  line Commissioner.
  line `26. Reference to High Court.`
  line `27. Hearing by High Court.`
  line `28. Appeal to Supreme Court.`
  line `28A. Tax to be paid notwithstanding reference, etc.`
  line `28B. Definition of High Court.`
  line `CHAPTER VII`
  line `P AYMENT AND RECOVERY OF GIFT-TAX`
  line `29. Gift-tax by whom payable.`
  line `30. Gift-tax to be charged on property gifted.`
  line `31. Notice of demand.`
  line `32. Recovery of tax and penalties.`
  line `33. Mode of recovery.`
  line `CHAPTER VIIA`
  line `R EFUNDS`
  line `33A. Refunds.`
  line `CHAPTER VIII`
  line `M ISCELLANEOUS`
  line `34. Rectification of mistakes.`
  line `35. Prosecution.`
  line `35A. Offences by companies.`
  line `35B. Offences by Hindu undivided families.`
  line `35C. Section 360 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973, and the Probation of Offenders`
  line `Act, 1958, not to apply.`
  line `35D. Presumption as to culpable mental state.`
  line `35E. Proof of entries in records or documents.`
  line `36. Power regarding discovery, production of evidence, etc.`
  line `37. Power to call for information.`
  line `38. Effect of transfer of authorities on pending proceedings.`
  line `39. Computation of period of limitation.`
  line `40. Service of notice.`
