  string
  line 4
  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `41. [ Omitted.].`
  line `41A. Publication of information respecting assessees.`
  line `41B. Disclosure of information respecting assessees.`
  line `41C. Return of gifts, etc., not to be invalid on certain grounds.`
  line `42. Bar of suits in civil court.`
  line `43. Appearance before gift-tax authorities by authorised representatives.`
  line `43A. Appearance by registered valuer in certain matters.`
  line `44. Agreement for avoidance or relief of double taxation with respect to gift-tax.`
  line `44A. Rounding off of taxable gifts.`
  line `44B. Rounding off of tax, etc.`
  line `45. Act not to apply in certain cases.`
  line `46. Power to make rules.`
  line `46A. Power to make exemption, etc., in relation to certain Union territories.`
  line `47. Power to remove difficulties.`
  line `SCHEDULE I.`
  line `SCHEDULE II.`
