obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line 5
  line `THE GIFT-TAX ACT, 1958`
  line `A CT N O. 18 OF 1958`
  line `[15 th May, 1958.]`
  line `An Act to provide for the levy of gift-tax.`
  line `B E it enacted by Parliament in the Ninth Year of the Republic of India as follows: —`
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `1. Short title, extent and commencement. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called the Gift-tax Act, 1958.`
  line `( 2 ) It extends to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*.`
  line `( 3 ) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 1st day of April, 1958.`
  line `2. Definitions. — In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `2 [( ii ) “Appellate Tribunal” means the Appellate Tribunal constituted under section 252 of the`
  line `Income-tax Act;`
  line `( iii ) “assessee” means a person by whom gift -tax or any other sum of money is payable under`
  line `this Act, and includes —`
  line `( a ) every person in respect of whom any proceeding under this Act has been taken for the`
  line `determination of gift-tax payable by him or by any other person or the amount of refund due to`
  line `him or such other person;`
  line `( b ) every person who is deemed to be an assessee under this Act;`
  line `( c ) every person who is deemed to be an assessee in default under this Act;`
  line `3 [( iiia ) “Assessing Officer” means the 4 [Assistant Commissioner or Deputy Commissioner] or`
  line `the Income-tax Officer who is vested with the relevant jurisdiction by virtue of directions or orders`
  line `issued under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) of section 120 or any other provision of the`
  line `Income-tax Act which apply for the purposes of gift-tax under section 7 of this Act, and also the`
  line `5 [Joint Commissioner] who is directed under clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 4 ) of the said section 120 to`
  line `exercise or perform all or any of the powers and functions conferred on or assigned to the Assessing`
  line `Officer under that Act;]`
  line `( iv ) “assessment” includ es reassessment;`
  line `* Subject to verification and confirmation by the Administrative ministry.`
  line `1. Clause ( i ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 162 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 2, for clauses ( ii ), ( iii ) and ( iv ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 162 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 76, for “Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 76, ibid., for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-6
