  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  sourcePage 6
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line 6
  line `( iva ) “assessment year” means the period of twelve months commencing on the 1st day of April`
  line `every year;]`
  line `( v ) “Board” means the 1 [Central Board of Direct Taxes constituted under the Central Boards of`
  line `Revenue Act, 1963 (54 of 1963)];`
  line `2 [( va ) “charitable purpose” includes relief of the poor, education, medical relief, and the`
  line `advancement of any other object of general public utility 3 ***;]`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `6 [( vii ) the expressions “company”, “Indian company” and “company in which the public are`
  line `substantially interested” shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them under section 2 of the`
  line `Income-tax Act;]`
  line `7 * * * * *`
  line `( viii ) “donee” means any person who acquires any property under a gift, and, where a gift is`
  line `made to a trustee for the benefit of another person, includes both the trustee and the beneficiary;`
  line `( ix ) “donor” means any person who makes a gift;`
  line `( x ) “executor” means an executor or administrator of the estate of a deceased person;`
  line `8 [( xi ) the expressions “firm”, “partner” and “partnership” shall have the meanings respectively`
  line `assigned to them under section 2 of the Income-tax Act;]`
  line `( xii ) “gift” means the transfer by one person to another of any existing movable or immovable`
  line `property made voluntarily and without consideration in money or money’s worth, and 9 [includes the`
  line `transfer or conversion of any property referred to in section 4, deemed to be a gift under that section].`
  line `10 [ Explanation. — A transfer of any building or part thereof referred to in clause ( iii ), clause ( iiia )`
  line `or clause ( iiib ) of section 27 of the Income-tax Act by the person who is deemed under the said clause`
  line `to be the owner thereof made voluntarily and without consideration in money or money’s worth, shall`
  line `be deemed to be a gift made by such person;]`
  line `11 * * * * *`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1963, s. 5 for “Central Board of Revenue constituted under the Central Board of Revenue Act, 1924”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-1-1964).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `3. The words “not involving the carrying on of any activity for profit” omitted by Act 67 of 1984, s. 71 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1984).`
  line `4. Clause ( vi ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 162 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `5. Clause ( via ) omitted by s. 162, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 162, ibid., for clause ( vii ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `7. Clause ( viia ) omitted by s. 162, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 162, ibid., for clause ( xi ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 32 of 1971, s. 37, for “includes the transfer of any property deemed to be a gift under section 4”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 90 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `11. Clause ( xiii ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 162 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  kind page
