  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  sourcePage 7
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line 7
  line `1 [( xiv ) “ Income- tax Act” means the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961);]`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `5 [( xvib ) “legal representative” has the meaning assigned to it in clause ( 11 ) of section 2 of the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908);]`
  line `6 * * * * *`
  line `( xviii ) “person” includes a Hindu undivided family or a company or an association or a body of`
  line `individuals or persons, whether incorporated or not;`
  line `( xix ) “prescribed” means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line `( xx ) “previous year”, in relation to any assessment year—`
  line `( a ) in the case of an assessee 7 [having no source of income, profits or gains or] having a`
  line `source of income, profits or gains in respect of which there is no previous year under the`
  line `Income-tax Act, means the twelve months ending on the 31st day of March immediately`
  line `preceding the assessment year;`
  line `8 * * * * *`
  line `( c ) in the case of any other assessee, means the previous year as defined in 9 [section 3] of the`
  line `Income-tax Act if an assessment were to be made under that Act for that year:`
  line `10 [Provided that where a person who has not been assessed under this Act for any assessment`
  line `year makes a gift on a date which does not fall within a previous year as defined in`
  line `sub-clause ( a ) 11 *** or sub-clause ( c ), the previous year shall be the twelve months ending on the`
  line `31st day of March immediately preceding the assessment year;`
  line `12 * * * * * ]`
  line `( xxi ) “principal officer”, used with reference to a company or any association of persons,`
  line `means —`
  line `( a ) the secretary and treasurer, manager, managing agent, managing director or agent of the`
  line `company or association; or`
  line `( b ) any person connected with the management of the affairs of the company or association`
  line `upon whom the 13 [Assessing Officer] has served a notice of his intention of treating him as the`
  line `principal officer thereof;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 2, for clause ( xiv ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `2. Clause ( xv ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 162 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Clause ( xvi ) omitted by, s. 162, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. Clause ( xvia ) omitted by, s. 162, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `6. Clause ( xvii ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 162 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 12 of 1959, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-1959).`
  line `8. Sub-clause ( b ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 162 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 2, for “clause ( 11 ) of section 2” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1963).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 12 of 1959, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-1959).`
  line `11. The words “or sub -clause ( b )” omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 162 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `12. The Second proviso omitted by s.162, ibid, (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `13. Subs. by s. 161, ibid., for “Gift - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-8
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Page 8`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  sourcePage 8
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line 8
  line `( xxii ) “property” includes any interest in property, movable or immovable;`
  line `( xxiii ) “taxable gifts” means gifts chargeable to gift -tax under this Act;`
  line `1 [( xxiiia ) territories to which this Act extends shall be deemed to include the Union territories of`
  line `Dadra and Nagar Haveli, Goa, Daman and Diu, and Pondicherry —`
  line `( a ) as respects any period for the purposes of section 5; and`
  line `( b ) as respects any period included in the previous year, for the purposes of making any`
  line `assessment for the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1963, or for any`
  line `subsequent year;]`
  line `( xxiv ) “transfer of property” means any disposition, conveyance, assignment, settlement,`
  line `delivery, payment or other alienation of property and, without limiting the generality of the foregoing,`
  line `includes —`
  line `( a ) the creation of a trust in property;`
  line `( b ) the grant or creation of any lease, mortgage, charge, easement, licence, power,`
  line `partnership or interest in property;`
  line `( c ) the exercise of a power of appointment 2 [(whether general, special or subject to any`
  line `restrictions as to the persons in whose favour the appointment may be made)] of property vested`
  line `in any person, not the owner of the property, to determine its disposition in favour of any person`
  line `other than the donee of the power; and`
  line `( d ) any transaction entered into by any person with intent thereby to diminish directly or`
  line `indirectly the value of his own property and to increase the value of the property of any other`
  line person;
  line `3 [( xxv ) the expressions “Chief Commissioner”, “Director General”, “Commissioner”,`
  line `“Commissioner (Appeals)”, “Director”, 4 [“Additional Director of Income - tax”, “Additional`
  line `Commissioner of Income- tax”, “Additional Commissioner of Income - tax (Appeals)”, “ 5 [Joint`
  line `Director ” ]] 6 [ “ Joint Commissioner” ], “Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)”, 7 [ “Assistant Commissioner`
  line `or Deputy Commissioner ” ], “Income - tax Officer”, “Tax Recovery Officer” and “Inspector of`
  line `Income- tax” shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them under section 2 of the Income -tax`
  line Act.]
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `C HARGE OF GIFT-TAX AND GIFTS SUBJECT TO SUCH CHARGE`
  line `3. Charge of gift-tax. — 8 [( 1 )] Subject to the other provisions contained in this Act, there shall be`
  line `charged for every 9 [assessment year] commencing on and from the 1st day of April, 1958, 10 [but before`
  line `the 1st day of April, 1987,] a tax (hereinafter referred to as gift-tax) in respect of the gifts, if any, made by`
  line `1. Ins. by The Taxation Laws (Extension to Union Territories) Regulation, 1963 (3 of 1963), by s. 3 and the Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-4-1980).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 162 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 54 (w.e.f. 1-6-1994).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 76 for “Deputy Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 76, ibid., for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 76, ibid., for “Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `8. Section 3 renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 23 of 1986, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 3, for “financial year” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1963).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 23 of 1986, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
