obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line 9
  line `a person during the previous year (other than gifts made before the 1st day of April, 1957), at the rate or`
  line `rates specified in 1 [Schedule I].`
  line `2 [( 2 ) 3 [Subject to the other provisions (including provisions for the levy of additional gift-tax)`
  line `contained in this Act], there shall be charged for every assessment year commencing on and from the 1st`
  line `day of April, 1987, gift-tax in respect of the gifts, if any, made by a person during the previous year, at the`
  line `rate of thirty per cent. on the value of all taxable gifts.]`
  line `4 [( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 2 ), the provisions of this Act shall cease to`
  line `apply and shall have no effect whatsoever in respect of any gift made on or after the 1st day of October,`
  line 1998.]
  line `4. Gifts to include certain transfers. — 5 [( 1 )] For the purposes of this Act, —`
  line `( a ) where property is transferred otherwise than for adequate consideration, the amount by`
  line `which the 6 [value of the property as on the date of the transfer and determined in the manner laid`
  line `down in Schedule II,] exceeds the value of the consideration shall be deemed to be a gift made by the`
  line `transferor:`
  line `7 [Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall apply in any case where the property is`
  line `transferred to the Government or where the value of the consideration for the transfer is determined or`
  line `approved by the Central Government or the Reserve Bank of India;]`
  line `( b ) where property is transferred for a consideration which, having regard to the circumstances of`
  line `the case, has not passed or is not intended to pass either in full or in part from the transferee to the`
  line `transferor, the amount of the consideration which has not passed or is not intended to pass shall be`
  line `deemed to be a gift made by the transferor;`
  line `( c ) where there is a release, discharge, surrender, forfeiture or abandonment of any debt, contract`
  line `or other actionable claim or of any interest in property by any person, the value of the release,`
  line `discharge, surrender, forfeiture or abandonment to the extent to which it has not been found to the`
  line `satisfaction of the 8 [Assessing Officer] to have been bona fide, shall be deemed to be a gift made by`
  line `the person responsible for the release, discharge, surrender, forfeiture or abandonment;`
  line `( d ) where a person absolutely entitled to property causes or has caused the same to be vested in`
  line `whatever manner in himself and any other person jointly without adequate consideration and such`
  line `other person makes an appropriation from or out of the said property, the amount of the appropriation`
  line `used for the benefit of the person making the appropriation or for the benefit of any other person shall`
  line `be deemed to be a gift made in his favour by the person who causes or has caused the property to be`
  line `so vested;`
  line `9 [( e ) where a person who has an interest in property as a tenant for a term or for life or a`
  line `remainderman surrenders or relinquishes his interest in the property or otherwise allows his interest to`
  line `be terminated without consideration or for a consideration which is not adequate, the value of the`
  line `interest so surrendered, relinquished or allowed to be terminated or, as the case may be, the amount`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 79, for “the Schedule” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 1986, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 163, for “Subject to the other provisions contained in this Act” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 75 (w.e.f. 1-1-1998).`
  line `5. Section 4 renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 32 of 1971, s. 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 84, for “market value of the property at the date of the transfer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1992).`
  line `7. The Proviso ins. by Act 25 of 1975, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Gift - tax officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-4-1980).`
