obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line 10
  line `by which such value exceeds the consideration received, shall be deemed to be a gift made by such`
  line person.]
  line `1 [( 2 ) Where, in the case of an individual being a member of a Hindu undivided family, any property`
  line `having been the separate property of the individual has been converted by the individual into property`
  line `belonging to the family through the act of impressing such separate property with the character of`
  line `property belonging to the family or throwing it into the common stock of the family (such property being`
  line `hereafter in this sub-section referred to as the converted property), then, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other provision of this Act or any other law for the time being in force, for the purpose of`
  line `computation of the taxable gifts made by the individual, the individual shall be deemed to have made a`
  line `gift of so much of the converted property as the members of the Hindu undivided family other than such`
  line `individual would be entitled to, if a partition of the converted property had taken place immediately after`
  line `such conversion.]`
  line `5. Exemption in respect of certain gifts. — ( 1 ) Gift-tax shall not be charged under this Act in`
  line `respect of gifts made by any person —`
  line `( i ) of immovable property situate outside the territories to which this Act extends;`
  line `( ii ) of movable property situate outside the said territories unless the person —`
  line `( a ) being an individual, is a citizen of India and is ordinarily resident in the said territories, or`
  line `( b ) not being an individual, is resident in the said territories, during the previous year in`
  line `which the gift is made;`
  line `2 [( iia ) being an individual who is not resident in India, to any person resident in India, of foreign`
  line `currency or other foreign exchange as defined respectively, in clause ( c ) and clause ( d ) of section 2 of`
  line `the Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1947 (7 of 1947), remitted from a country outside India in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of the said Act and any rules made thereunder, during the period`
  line `commencing on the 26th day of October, 1965, and ending on the 28th day of February, 1966, or such`
  line `later date as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this`
  line behalf.
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, the expression “resident in India” shall have the`
  line `meaning assigned to it in the Income-tax Act;]`
  line `3 [( iib ) being a person resident outside India, out of the moneys standing to his credit in a`
  line `Non-resident (External) Account in any bank in India in accordance with the provisions of the`
  line `Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973), and any rules made thereunder.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, “person resident outside India” has the meaning`
  line `assigned to it in clause ( q ) of section 2 of the Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973);`
  line `( iic ) being a citizen of India, or a person of Indian origin, who is not resident in India, to any`
  line `relative of such person in India, of convertible foreign exchange remitted from a country outside India`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of the Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973), and`
  line `any rules made thereunder.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause and clause ( iid ), —`
  line `( a ) a person shall be deemed to be of Indian origin if he or either of his parents or any of his`
  line `grand-parents was born in undivided India;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 1971, s. 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 1966, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-4-1966).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 14 of 1982, s. 38 (w.e.f. 1-4-1983).`
