obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line 11
  line `( b ) “convertible foreign exchange” means foreign exchange which is for the time being`
  line `treated by the Reserve Bank of India as convertible foreign exchange for the purposes of the`
  line `Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973), and any rules made thereunder;`
  line `( c ) “relative” has the meaning assigned to it in clause ( 41 ) of section 2 of the Income-tax`
  line Act;
  line `( d ) “ resident of India” shall have the meaning assigned to it in the Income -tax Act;]`
  line `( iid ) being a citizen of India or a person of Indian origin, who is not resident in India, to any`
  line `relative of such person in India of property in the form of 1 [any foreign exchange asset as defined in`
  line `clause ( b ) of section 115C of the Income-tax Act];]`
  line `2 [( iie ) being an individual who is a non-resident Indian, once out of the moneys standing to his`
  line `credit in an account opened and operated in accordance with the Non-resident (Non-repatriable)`
  line `Rupee Deposit Scheme, 1992.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, “non - resident Indian” shall have the meaning`
  line `assigned to it in clause ( e ) of section 115C of the Income-tax Act;]`
  line `( iii ) of property in the form of savings certificates issued by the Central Government, which that`
  line `Government, by notification in the Official Gazette exempts from gift-tax;`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 [( iiib ) of property in the form of Special Bearer Bonds, 1991;]`
  line `5 [( iiic ) 6 [being an individual or a Hindu undivided family, of property in the form of such Capital`
  line `Investment Bonds] as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in`
  line `this behalf subject to a maximum of rupees ten lakhs in value in the aggregate in one or more`
  line `previous years:`
  line `Provided that the exemption conferred by this clause shall be available only to a person who has`
  line `initially subscribed to the said bonds;]`
  line `7 [( iiid ) being an individual or a Hindu undivided family, of property in the form of such Relief`
  line `Bonds, as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf`
  line `subject to a maximum of rupees five lakhs in value in the aggregate in one or more previous years:`
  line `Provided that the exemption conferred by this clause shall be available only to a person who has`
  line `initially subscribed to the said Bonds;]`
  line `8 [( iiie ) being an individual who is a non-resident Indian, 9 [of property in the form of the bonds`
  line `specified under sub-clause ( iid ) of clause ( 15 ) of section 10 of the Income-tax Act:`
  line `Provided that] where an individual, who is a non-resident Indian in any previous year in which`
  line `the bonds are acquired, becomes a resident in India in any subsequent year, the provisions of this`
  line `clause shall apply in respect of the gifts of property referred to in this clause in such subsequent year`
  line `or any year thereafter.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 1983, s. 42, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-1984).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 38 of 1993, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `3. Clause ( iiia ) omitted by Act 23 of 1986, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 7 of 1981, s. 7 (w.e.f. 12-1-1981).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 14 of 1982, s. 38 (w.e.f. 1-4-1983).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 12 of 1983, s. 42 for “of property in the form of such Capital Investment Bonds” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1983).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 67 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 80 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 85, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
