obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line 12
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, the expressions —`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `( b ) “ non- resident Indian” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( e ) of section 115C`
  line `of the Income-tax Act;]`
  line `( iv ) to the Government or any local authority 2 [or any authority referred to in clause ( 20A ) of`
  line `section 10 of the Income-tax Act;]`
  line `( v ) to any institution or fund established 3 [or deemed to be established] for a charitable purpose`
  line `to which the provisions of 4 [section 80G] of the Income-tax Act apply;`
  line `5 [( va ) ( i ) to such temple, mosque, gurdwara, church or other place as has been notified by the`
  line `Central Government for the purposes of 6 [clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 80G of the`
  line `Income-tax Act]; or`
  line `( ii ) by way of settlement on trust, of property, the income from which, according to the deed`
  line `of settlement, is to be used exclusively in connection with the temple, mosque, gurdwara, church`
  line `or other place specified therein and notified as aforesaid;]`
  line `7 * * * * *`
  line `( vii ) to any relative dependent upon him for support and maintenance, on the occasion of the`
  line `marriage of the relative, subject to a maximum of rupees 8 [one hundred thousand] in value in respect`
  line `of the marriage of each such relative;`
  line `9 * * * * *`
  line `10 * * * * *`
  line `( x ) under a will;`
  line `( xi ) in contemplation of death;`
  line `( xii ) for the education of his children, to the extent to which the gifts are proved to the`
  line `satisfaction of the 11 [Assessing Officer] as being reasonable having regard to the circumstances of the`
  line case;
  line `( xiii ) being an employer, to any employee by way of bonus, gratuity or pension or to the`
  line `dependants of a deceased employee, to the extent to which the payment of such bonus, gratuity or`
  line `pension is proved to the satisfaction of the 11 [Assessing Officer] as being reasonable having regard to`
  line `the circumstances of the case and is made solely in recognition of the services rendered by the`
  line employee;
  line `12 * * * * *`
  line `1. Clause ( a ) omitted by Act 49 of 1991, s. 85 (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 66 of 1976, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1-4-1977).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 21 of 1973, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-1974).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 1971, s. 37, for “section 88” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1968).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 10 of 1965, s. 71 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 43 of 1971, s. 37, for “sub -section ( 6 ) of section 88 of the Income- tax Act, 1961” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1968).`
  line `7. Clause ( vi ) omitted by 23 of 1986, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 55, for “thirty thousand” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1995).`
  line `9. Clause ( viii ) omitted by 23 of 1986, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `10. Clause ( ix ) omitted, s. 42, ibid, (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Gift - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `12. Clause ( xiv ) omitted by 23 of 1986, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
