obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line 13
  line `( xv ) to any person in charge of any such Bhoodan or Sampattidan movement as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify.`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `2 [( 1A ) Any reference in clause ( v ) 3 *** of sub-section ( 1 ) to charitable purpose in relation to a gift`
  line `made on or after the 1st day of April, 1964, shall be construed as not including a purpose the whole or`
  line `substantially the whole of which is of a religious nature.]`
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section ( 1 ), gift-tax shall not be charged`
  line `under this Act in respect of gifts made by any person during the previous year, subject to a maximum of`
  line `rupees 4 [thirty thousand] in value.`
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) an individual shall be deemed to be ordinarily resident in the territories to which this Act`
  line `extends during the previous year in which the gift is made if during that year he is regarded as a`
  line `resident but not as not ordinarily resident 6 [within the meaning of section 6 of the Income-tax Act,`
  line `subject to the modification that references in that section to India shall be construed as references to`
  line `the territories to which this Act extends];`
  line `( b ) a Hindu undivided family, firm or other association of persons shall be deemed to be resident`
  line `in the territories to which this Act extends during any previous year unless, during that year, the`
  line `control and management of its affairs was situated wholly outside the said territories;`
  line `( c ) a company shall be deemed to be resident in the territories to which this Act extends during`
  line `the previous year, if —`
  line `( i ) it is a company formed and registered under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or is`
  line `an existing company within the meaning of that Act; or`
  line `( ii ) during that year, the control and management of that company was situated wholly in the`
  line `said territories;`
  line `( d ) “gifts made in contemplation of death” has the same meaning as in section 191 of the Indian`
  line `Succession Act, 1925 (39 of 1925).`
  line `7 [ 6. Value of gifts, how determined. — ( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ), the value of`
  line `any property, other than cash, transferred by way of gift shall, for the purpose of this Act, be its value as`
  line `on the date on which the gift was made and shall be determined in the manner laid down in Schedule II.`
  line `( 2 ) Where a person makes a gift which is not revocable for a specified period, the value of the`
  line `property gifted shall be the capitalised value of the income from such property during the period for`
  line `which the gift is not revocable.]`
  line `6A. [ Aggregation of gifts made during a certain period. ] — Omitted by the Finance Act, 1986 (23 of`
  line `1986), s. 43 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `1. Clause ( xvi ) omitted by 23 of 1986, s. 42, (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 15 of 1965, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-1964).`
  line `3. The words, brackets and figures “ or clause ( vi ) ” omitted by Act 23 of 1986, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 38 of 19 93, s. 41, for “twenty thousand” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1994).`
  line `5. Sub-section ( 3 ) omitted by 23 of 1986, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 4, for “in the taxable territories with the meaning of the income - tax Act” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1963).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 81, for section 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
