obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line 14
  line `CHAPTER III`
  line `G IFT-TAX AUTHORITIES`
  line `1 [ 7. Gift-tax authorities and their jurisdiction. — The income-tax authorities specified in`
  line `section 116 of the Income-tax Act shall be the gift-tax authorities for the purposes of this Act and every`
  line `such authority shall exercise the powers and perform the functions of a gift-tax authority under this Act in`
  line `respect of any person within his jurisdiction, and for this purpose his jurisdiction under this Act shall be`
  line `the same as he has under the Income-tax Act by virtue of orders or directions issued under section 120 of`
  line `that Act (including orders or directions assigning concurrent jurisdiction) or under any other provision of`
  line `that Act.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, the gift-tax authority having jurisdiction in relation to`
  line `a person who has no income assessable to income-tax under the Income-tax Act shall be the gift-tax`
  line `authority having jurisdiction in respect of the area in which that person resides.`
  line `7A. [Powers of Commissioner respecting specified areas, cases, persons, etc.] — Omitted by the`
  line `Direct Tax Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1988 (4 of 1988), s. 165 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `7AA. [ Concurrent jurisdiction of Inspecting Assistant Commissioner and Gift-tax Officer. ] —`
  line `Omitted by s. 165, ibid. ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `7B. [ Power to transfer cases. ] — Omitted by s. 165, ibid. ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `8. Control of gift-tax authorities. — Section 118 of the Income-tax Act and any notification issued`
  line `thereunder shall apply in relation to the control of gift-tax authorities as they apply in relation to the`
  line `control of the corresponding income-tax authorities, except to the extent to which the Board may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, otherwise direct in respect of any gift-tax authority.`
  line `8A. [ Commissioners of gift-tax Appeals. ] — Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1988`
  line `(4 of 1988), s. 165 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `9. Instructions to subordinate authorities. — ( 1 ) The Board may, from time to time, issue such`
  line `orders, instructions and directions to other gift-tax authorities as it may deem fit for the proper`
  line `administration of this Act, and such authorities and all other persons employed in the execution of this`
  line `Act shall observe and follow such orders, instructions and directions of the Board:`
  line `Provided that no such orders, instructions or directions shall be issued —`
  line `( a ) so as to require any gift-tax authority to make a particular assessment or to dispose of a`
  line `particular case in a particular manner; or`
  line `( b ) so as to interfere with the discretion of the Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals) in the exercise of his appellate functions.`
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, —`
  line `( a ) the Board may, if it considers it necessary or expedient so to do, for the purpose of proper and`
  line `efficient management of the work of assessment and collection of revenue, issue, from time to time`
  line `(whether by way of relaxation of any of the provisions of sections 2 [13, 14, 15, 16, 16B,] 17 and 34`
  line `or otherwise), general or special orders in respect of any class of cases, setting forth directions or`
  line `instructions (not being prejudicial to assessees) as to the guidelines, principles or procedures to be`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 164, for sections 7, 8, 9 and 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 59, for “15, 16” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1990).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-15
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Page 15`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  sourcePage 15
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line 15
  line `followed by other gift-tax authorities in the work relating to assessment or collection of revenue or`
  line `the initiation of proceedings for the imposition of penalties and any such order may, if the Board is of`
  line `opinion that it is necessary in the public interest so to do, be published and circulated in the prescribed`
  line `manner for general information;`
  line `( b ) the Board may, if it considers it desirable or expedient so to do for avoiding genuine hardship`
  line `in any case or class of cases, by general or special order, authorise any gift-tax authority, not being a`
  line `Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or Commissioner (Appeals) to admit an application or claim for any`
  line `exemption, deduction, refund or any other relief under this Act after the expiry of the period specified`
  line `by or under this Act for making such application or claim and deal with the same on merits in`
  line `accordance with law.]`
  line `9A. [ Directors of Inspection. ] — Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1988`
  line `(4 of 1988), s. 165 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `10. Jurisdiction of Assessing Officers and power to transfer cases. — ( 1 ) The provisions of`
  line `sections 124 and 127 of the Income-tax Act shall, so far as may be, apply for the purposes of this Act as`
  line `they apply for the purposes of the Income-tax Act, subject to the modifications specified in`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ).`
  line `( 2 ) The modifications referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be the following, namely: —`
  line `( a ) in section 124 of the Income-tax Act, —`
  line `( i ) in sub-section ( 3 ), references to the provisions of the Income-tax Act shall be`
  line `construed as references to the corresponding provisions of the Gift-tax Act;`
  line `( ii ) sub-section ( 5 ) shall be omitted;`
  line `( b ) in section 127 of the Income-tax Act, in the Explanation below sub-section 1 [( 4 )]`
  line `references to proceedings under the Income-tax Act shall be construed as including references to`
  line `proceedings under the Gift-tax Act.]`
  line `11. [ Inspector of Gift-tax. ] — Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1988 (4 of 1988), s.`
  line `165 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `11A. [ Commissioner competent to perform any function or functions. ] — Omitted by s. 165, ibid.`
  line `( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `11AA. [ Gift-tax Officer competent to perform any function or functions. ] — Omitted by s. 165, ibid.`
  line `( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `11B. [ Control of gift-tax authorities. ] — Omitted by s. 165, ibid. ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `12. [ Gift-tax authorities to follow orders, etc., of the Board. ] — Omitted by s. 165, ibid. ( w.e.f. 1-4-`
  line `1988).`
  line `2 [ 12A. Power of 3 [ Chief Commissioner or Commissioner ] and of 4 [ 5 [Joint Commissioner] to`
  line `make enquiries under this Act. — The 3 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner] and the 4 [ 5 [Joint`
  line `Commissioner] shall be competent to make any enquiry under this Act, and for this purpose, shall have`
  line `all the powers that an 6 [Assessing Officer] has under this Act in relation to the making of enquiries.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 82, for “( 5 )” ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Commissioner of Gift - tax” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 161, ibid., for “Inspecting Assistant Commissioner of Gift - tax” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 76, for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, ibid., for “Gift - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
