  sourcePage 16
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line 16
  line `CHAPTER IV`
  line `A SSESSMENT`
  line `13. Return of gifts. — 1 [( 1 ) Every person who during a previous year has made any taxable gifts, or`
  line `is assessable in respect of the taxable gifts made by any other person under this Act, which, in either case,`
  line `exceeded the maximum amount not chargeable to gift-tax, shall, on or before the 30th day of June of the`
  line `corresponding assessment year, furnish a return of such gifts in the prescribed form and verified in the`
  line `prescribed manner and setting forth such other particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, a return which shows the`
  line `amount of taxable gifts below the maximum amount which is not chargeable to tax shall be deemed never`
  line `to have been furnished:`
  line `Provided that this sub-section shall not apply to a return furnished in response to a notice under`
  line `section 16.]`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `3 [ 14. Return after due date and amendment of return. — If any person has not furnished a return`
  line `within the time allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 13 or by a notice issued under clause ( i ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 4 ) of section 15, or having furnished a return discovers any omission or wrong statement`
  line `therein, he may furnish a return or a revised return, as the case may be, at any time before the expiry of`
  line `one year from the end of the relevant assessment year or before the completion of the assessment,`
  line `whichever is earlier:`
  line `Provided that —`
  line `( a ) where such return or revised return relates to the assessment year commencing on the 1st day`
  line `of April, 1987, or any earlier assessment year, it may be furnished at any time up to and inclusive of`
  line `the 31st day of March, 1990 or before the completion of the assessment, whichever is earlier;`
  line `( b ) where such return or revised return relates to the assessment year commencing on the 1st day`
  line `of April, 1988, it may be furnished at any time up to and inclusive of the 31st day of March, 1991, or`
  line `before the completion of the assessment, whichever is earlier.]`
  line `4 [ 14A. Return by whom to be signed. — The return made under section 13 or section 14 shall be`
  line `signed and verified —`
  line `5 [( a ) in the case of an individual, —`
  line `( i ) by the individual himself;`
  line `( ii ) where he is absent from India, by the individual himself or by some person duly`
  line `authorised by him in this behalf;`
  line `( iii ) where he is mentally incapacitated from attending to his affairs, by his guardian or any`
  line `other person competent to act on his behalf; and`
  line `( iv ) where, for any other reason, it is not possible for the individual to sign the return, by any`
  line `person duly authorised by him in this behalf:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 166, for sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Sub-section ( 3 ) omitted by s. 166, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 167, ibid., for section 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 168, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
