obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line 17
  line `Provided that in a case referred to in sub-clause ( ii ) or sub-clause ( iv ), the person signing the`
  line `return holds a valid power of attorney from the individual to do so, which shall be attached to the`
  line return;]
  line `( b ) in the case of a Hindu undivided family, by the karta, and, where the karta is absent from`
  line `India or is mentally incapacitated from attending to his affairs, by any other adult member of such`
  line family;
  line `1 [( c ) in the case of a company, by the managing director thereof or where for any unavoidable`
  line `reason such managing director is not able to sign and verify the return, or where there is no managing`
  line `director, by any director thereof:`
  line `2 [Provided that where the company is not resident in India, the return may be signed and verified`
  line `by a person who holds a valid power of attorney from such company to do so, which shall be attached`
  line `to the return:`
  line `Provided further that, —`
  line `( a ) where the company is being wound up, whether under the orders of the court or`
  line `otherwise, or where any person has been appointed as the receiver of any assets of the company,`
  line `the return shall be signed and verified by the liquidator referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section`
  line `178 of the Income-tax Act;`
  line `( b ) where the management of the company has been taken over by the Central Government`
  line `or any State Government under any law, the return of the company shall be signed and verified by`
  line `the principal officer thereof;]`
  line `( d ) in the case of a firm, by the managing partner thereof or where for any unavoidable`
  line `reason such managing partner is not able to sign and verify the return, or where there is no`
  line `managing partner as such, by any partner thereof, not being a minor;]`
  line `( e ) in the case of any other association, by any member of the association or the principal`
  line `officer thereof; and`
  line `( f ) in the case of any other person, by that person, or by some person competent to act on his`
  line behalf.]
  line `3 [ 14B. Self-assessment. — ( 1 ) Where any tax is payable on the basis of any return furnished under`
  line `section 13 or under section 14 or in response to a notice under clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 4 ) of section 15`
  line `or under section 16, after taking into account the amount of tax, if any, already paid under any provision`
  line `of this Act, the assessee shall be liable to pay such tax, together with interest payable under any provision`
  line `of this Act for any delay in furnishing the return, before furnishing the return and the return shall be`
  line `accompanied by proof of payment of such tax and interest.`
  line `Explanation. — Where the amount paid by the assessee under this sub-section falls short of the`
  line `aggregate of the tax and interest as aforesaid, the amount so paid shall first be adjusted towards the`
  line `interest payable as aforesaid and the balance, if any, shall be adjusted towards the tax payable.`
  line `( 2 ) After the regular assessment under section 15 has been made, any amount paid under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to have been paid towards such regular assessment.`
  line `( 3 ) If any assessee fails to pay the whole or any part of such tax or interest or both in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ), he shall, without prejudice to any other consequences which he may`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 111, for clauses ( c ) and ( d ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `2. The provisos added by Act 4 of 1988, s. 168 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 169, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
