obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line 18
  line `incur, be deemed to be an assessee in default in respect of the tax or interest or both remaining unpaid and`
  line `all the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly.]`
  line `1 [( 4 ) The provisions of this section shall apply in respect of assessment for the assessment year`
  line `commencing on the 1st day of April, 1989 and subsequent assessment years.]`
  line `2 [15. Assessment. — ( 1 ) ( a ) Where a return has been made under section 13 or section 14 or in`
  line `response to a notice under clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 4 ), —`
  line `( i ) if any tax or interest is found due on the basis of such return after adjustment of any amount`
  line `paid by way of tax or interest, an intimation shall be sent to the assessee specifying the sum so`
  line `payable, and such intimation shall be deemed to be a notice issued under section 31 and all the`
  line `provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly; and`
  line `( ii ) if any refund is due on the basis of such return, it shall be granted to the assessee:`
  line `Provided that in computing the tax or interest payable by, or refundable to the assessee, the`
  line `following adjustments shall be made in the taxable gifts declared in the return, namely: —`
  line `( i ) any arithmetical errors in the return, accounts or documents accompanying it shall be`
  line rectified;
  line `( ii ) any exemption or deduction, which, on the basis of the information available in such`
  line `return, accounts or documents is prima facie admissible but which is not claimed or made in the`
  line `return, shall be allowed;`
  line `( iii ) any exemption or deduction claimed or made in the return, which, on the basis of the`
  line `information available in such return, accounts or documents, is prima facie inadmissible, shall be`
  line `disallowed:`
  line `3 [Provided further that where adjustments are made under the first proviso, an intimation shall be sent`
  line `to the assessee, notwithstanding that no tax or interest is found due from him after making the said`
  line `adjustments:]`
  line `4 [ 5 [Provided also] that an intimation for any tax or interest due under this clause shall not be sent`
  line `after the expiry of two years from the end of the assessment year in which the gifts were first assessable.]`
  line `( b ) Where as a result of an order made under 3 [sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 5 ) of this section or]`
  line `section 16 or section 22 or section 23 or section 24 or section 26 or section 28 or section 34 relating to`
  line `any earlier assessment year and passed subsequent to the filing of the return referred to in clause ( a ), there`
  line `is any variation in the exemption or deduction claimed or made in the return, and as a result of which, —`
  line `( i ) if any tax or interest is found due, an intimation shall be sent to the assessee specifying the`
  line `sum so payable, and such intimation shall be deemed to be a notice of demand issued under`
  line `section 31 and all the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly; and`
  line `( ii ) if any refund is due, it shall be granted to the assessee:`
  line `Provided that an intimation for any tax or interest due under this clause shall not be sent after the`
  line `expiry of four years from the end of the financial year in which any such order was passed.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 36 of 1989, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 170, for section 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 36 of 1989, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 83 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 36 of 1989, s. 32, for “provided further” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
