  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  sourcePage 19
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line 19
  line `1 [( 1A ) ( a ) Where in the case of any person, the taxable gift, as a result of the adjustments made under`
  line `2 [the first proviso] to clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ), exceeds the taxable gift declared in the return by any`
  line `amount, the Assessing Officer shall, —`
  line `( i ) further increase the amount of tax payable under sub-section ( 1 ) by an additional gift-tax`
  line `calculated at the rate of twenty per cent. of the tax payable on such excess amount and specify the`
  line `additional gift-tax in the intimation to be sent under sub-clause ( i ) of clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 );`
  line `( ii ) where any refund is due under sub-section ( 1 ), reduce the amount of such refund by an`
  line `amount equivalent to the additional gift-tax calculated under sub-clause ( i ).`
  line `( b ) Where as a result of an order under section 22 or section 23 or section 24 or section 26 or`
  line `section 28 or section 34, the amount on which additional gift-tax is payable under clause ( a ) has been`
  line `increased or reduced, as the case may be, the additional gift-tax shall be increased or reduced accordingly,`
  line `and, —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the additional gift-tax is increased, the Assessing Officer shall serve on the`
  line `assessee a notice of demand under section 31;`
  line `( ii ) in a case where the additional gift-tax is reduced, the excess amount paid, if any, shall be`
  line refunded.
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- section, “tax payable on such excess amount” means the`
  line `difference between the tax on the taxable gift and the tax that would have been chargeable had such`
  line `taxable gift been reduced by the amount of adjustments.]`
  line `3 [( 1B ) Where an assessee furnishes a revised return under section 14 after the issue of an intimation,`
  line `or the grant of refund, if any, under sub-section ( 1 ) of this section, the provisions of sub-sections ( 1 ) and`
  line `( 1A ) of this section shall apply in relation to such revised return and —`
  line `( i ) the intimation already sent for any gift-tax, additional gift-tax or interest shall be amended on`
  line `the basis of the said revised return and where any amount payable by way of gift-tax, additional`
  line `gift-tax or interest specified in the said intimation has already been paid by the assessee then, if any`
  line `such amendment has the effect of —`
  line `( a ) enhancing the amount already paid, the intimation amended under this clause shall be`
  line `sent to the assessee specifying the excess amount payable by him and such intimation shall be`
  line `deemed to be a notice of demand issued under section 31 and all the provisions of this Act, shall`
  line `apply accordingly;`
  line `( b ) reducing, the amount already paid, the excess amount paid shall be refunded to the`
  line assessee;
  line `( ii ) the amount of the refund already granted shall be enhanced or reduced on the basis of the`
  line `said revised return and where the amount of refund already granted is —`
  line `( a ) enhanced, only the excess amount of refund due to the assessee shall be paid to him;`
  line `( b ) reduced, the excess amount so refunded shall be deemed to be the tax payable by the`
  line `assessee and an intimation shall be sent to the assessee specifying the amount so payable, and`
  line `such intimation shall be deemed to be a notice of demand issued under section 31 and all the`
  line `provisions of this Act, shall apply accordingly:`
  line `Provided that an assessee, who has furnished a revised return under section 14 after the service`
  line `upon him of the intimation under sub-section ( 1 ) of this section, shall be liable to pay additional`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 83 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 36 of 1989, s. 32, for “the proviso” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 60 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
