obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line 20
  line `gift-tax in relation to the adjustments made under the first proviso to clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ) and`
  line `specified in the said intimation, whether or not he has made the said adjustments in the revised`
  line return.]
  line `( 2 ) 1 [Where a return has been made under section 13 or section 14 or in response to a notice under`
  line `clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 4 ) of this section, the Assessing Officer shall, if he] considers it necessary or`
  line `expedient to ensure that the assessee has not omitted to disclose any taxable gift or has not understated the`
  line `amount or value of any such gift or has not under-paid the tax in any manner, 2 [serve on the assessee] a`
  line `notice requiring him, on a date to be specified therein, either to attend at the office of the Assessing`
  line `Officer or to produce, or cause to be produced there, any evidence on which the assessee may rely in`
  line `support of the return:`
  line `3 [Provided that no notice under this sub-section shall be served on the assessee after the expiry of`
  line `twelve months from the end of the month in which the return is furnished.]`
  line `( 3 ) On the date specified in the notice issued under sub-section ( 2 ) or, as soon afterwards as may be,`
  line `after hearing such evidence as the assessee may produce and such other evidence as the Assessing Officer`
  line `may require on specified points, and after taking into account all relevant material which he has gathered,`
  line `the Assessing Officer shall, by order in writing, assess the value of taxable gifts made by the assessee and`
  line `determine the sum payable by him on the basis of such assessment.`
  line `( 4 ) For the purposes of making an assessment under this Act, the Assessing Officer may serve, on any`
  line `person who has made a return under section 13 or section 14 or in whose case the time allowed under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 13 for furnishing the return has expired, a notice requiring him, on a date to be`
  line `specified therein, —`
  line `( i ) where such person has not made a return 4 [within the time allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 13], to furnish a return of the taxable gifts made by him or of the taxable gifts made by any`
  line `other person in respect of which he is assessable under this Act during the previous year, in the`
  line `prescribed form and verified in the prescribed manner and setting forth such other particulars as may`
  line `be prescribed, or`
  line `( ii ) to produce or cause to be produced such accounts, records or other documents as the`
  line `Assessing Officer may require.`
  line `( 5 ) If any person, —`
  line `( a ) fails to make the return required under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 13 and has not made a return`
  line `or a revised return under section 14, or`
  line `( b ) fails to comply with all the terms of a notice issued under sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-section ( 4 ),`
  line `the Assessing Officer, after taking into account all relevant material which he has gathered, shall, after`
  line `giving such person an opportunity of being heard, estimate the value of taxable gifts to the best of his`
  line `judgment and determine the sum payable by such person on the basis of such assessment:`
  line `Provided that such opportunity shall be given by the Assessing Officer by serving a notice calling`
  line `upon the person to show cause on a date and time to be specified in the notice, why the assessment should`
  line `not be completed to the best of his judgment:`
  line `Provided further that it shall not be necessary to give such opportunity in a case where a notice under`
  line `sub-section ( 4 ) has been issued prior to the making of the assessment under this sub-section.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 36 of 1989, s. 32, for “In a case referred to in sub -section ( 1 ), if the Assessing Officer” (w.e. f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 32, ibid., for “he shall serve on the assessee” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 86, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 60, for “before the end of the relevant assessment year” (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
