obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line 21
  line `( 6 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 6, for the purpose of making an assessment under`
  line `this Act, 1 [where under the provisions of section 6 read with Schedule II, the fair market value of any`
  line `property transferred by way of gifts is to be taken into account in such assessment,] the Assessing Officer`
  line `may refer the valuation of such property to the Valuation Officer, —`
  line `( a ) in a case where the value of the property as returned is in accordance with the estimate made`
  line `by a registered valuer, if the Assessing Officer is of opinion that the value so returned is less than its`
  line `fair market value;`
  line `( b ) in any other case, if the Assessing Officer is of opinion —`
  line `( i ) that the fair market value of the property exceeds the value of the property as returned by`
  line `more than such percentage of the value of the property as returned or by more than such amount`
  line `as may be prescribed in this behalf; or`
  line `( ii ) that having regard to the nature of the property and other relevant circumstances, it is`
  line `necessary so to do,`
  line `and where any such reference is made, the provisions of sub-sections ( 2 ), ( 3 ), ( 4 ), ( 5 ) and ( 6 ) of`
  line `section 16A, clauses ( ha ) and ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) and sub-sections ( 3A ) and ( 4 ) of section 23,`
  line `sub-section ( 5 ) of section 24, section 34AA, section 35 and section 37 of the Wealth-tax Act, 1957`
  line `(27 of 1957), shall, with the necessary modifications, apply in relation to such reference as they apply in`
  line `relation to a reference made by the Assessing Officer under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 16A of that Act.`
  line `Explanation. — In this sub- section, “Valuation Officer” has the same meaning as in clause ( r ) of`
  line `section 2 of the Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957).]`
  line `2 [( 7 ) Where a regular assessment under sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 5 ) is made, —`
  line `( a ) any tax or interest paid by the assessee under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to have been`
  line `paid towards such regular assessments;`
  line `( b ) if no refund is due on regular assessment or the amount refunded under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `exceeds the amount refundable on regular assessment, the whole or the excess amount so refunded`
  line `shall be deemed to be tax payable by the assessee and the provisions of this Act shall apply`
  line accordingly.
  line `( 8 ) The provisions of this section, except those of sub-section ( 6 ), as they stood immediately before`
  line `their amendment by the Direct Tax Laws (Amendment) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988), shall apply to and in`
  line `relation to any assessment for the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1988, or any`
  line `earlier assessment year and references in this section to the other provisions of this Act shall be construed`
  line `as references to those provisions as for the time being in force and applicable to the relevant assessment`
  line year.]
  line `3 [ Explanation. — An intimation sent to the assessee under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 1B ) shall be`
  line `deemed to be an order for the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 24.]`
  line `16. Gift escaping assessment. — 4 [( 1 ) If the Assessing Officer 5 [has reasons to believe] that the`
  line `taxable gifts in respect of which any person is assessable under this Act, (whether made by him or by any`
  line `other person) have escaped assessment for any assessment year (whether by reason of under-assessment`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 83 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 36 of 1989, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 86 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 171, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 84, for “ for reasons to be recorded by him in writing, is of the opinion ” (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
