obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line 22
  line `or assessment at too low a rate or otherwise), he may, subject to the other provisions of this section and`
  line `section 16A, serve on such person a notice requiring him to furnish within such period, 1 *** as may be`
  line `specified in the notice, a return in the prescribed form and verified in the prescribed manner, setting forth`
  line `the taxable gifts made by him or by such other person during the previous year mentioned in the notice, in`
  line `respect of which he is assessable, along with such other particulars as may be required by the notice, and`
  line `may proceed to assess or re-assess such gifts and also any other taxable gifts in respect of which such`
  line `person is assessable, which have escaped assessment and which come to his notice subsequently in the`
  line `course of the proceedings under this section for the assessment year concerned (hereafter in this section`
  line `referred to as the relevant assessment year); and the provisions of this Act shall, so far as may be, apply as`
  line `if the return were a return required under section 13:`
  line `Provided that where an assessment under sub-section ( 3 ) of section 15 or this section has been made`
  line `for the relevant assessment year, no action shall be taken under this section after the expiry of four years`
  line `from the end of the relevant assessment year, unless any taxable gift chargeable to tax has escaped`
  line `assessment for such assessment year by reason of the failure on the part of the assessee to make a return`
  line `under section 13 or section 14 or in response to a notice issued under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 15 or this`
  line `section or to disclose fully and truly all material facts necessary for his assessment for that assessment`
  line `year:`
  line `2 [Provided further that the Assessing Officer shall, before issuing any notice under this sub-section,`
  line `record his reasons for doing so.]`
  line `Explanation. — Production before the Assessing Officer of account books or other evidence from`
  line `which material evidence could with due diligence have been discovered by the Assessing Officer will not`
  line `necessarily amount to disclosure within the meaning of the foregoing proviso.`
  line `( 1A ) No notice under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be issued for the relevant assessment year, —`
  line `( a ) in a case where an assessment under sub-section ( 3 ) of section 15 or sub-section ( 1 ) of this`
  line `section has been made for such assessment year, —`
  line `( i ) if four years have elapsed from the end of the relevant assessment year, unless the case`
  line `falls under sub-clause ( ii ) or sub-clause ( iii );`
  line `( ii ) if four years, but not more than seven years, have elapsed from the end of the relevant`
  line `assessment year, unless the value of taxable gifts chargeable to tax which have escaped`
  line `assessment amounts to or is likely to amount to rupees fifty thousand or more for that year;`
  line `( iii ) if seven years, but not more than ten years, have elapsed from the end of the relevant`
  line `assessment year, unless the value of taxable gifts chargeable to tax which have escaped`
  line `assessment amounts to or is likely to amount to rupees one lakh or more for that year;`
  line `( b ) in any other case, —`
  line `( i ) if four years have elapsed from the end of the relevant assessment year, unless the case`
  line `falls under sub-clause ( ii ) or sub-clause ( iii );`
  line `( ii ) if four years, but not more than seven years, have elapsed from the end of the relevant`
  line `assessment year, unless the value of taxable gifts chargeable to tax which have escaped`
  line `assessment amounts to or is likely to amount to rupees twenty-five thousand or more for that`
  line year;
  line `1. The words “ not being less than thirty days ” omitted by the Act 32 of 2003, s. 101, (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 84 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-23
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Page 23`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  sourcePage 23
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line 23
  line `( iii ) if seven years, but not more than ten years, have elapsed from the end of the relevant`
  line `assessment year, unless the value of taxable gifts chargeable to tax which have escaped`
  line `assessment amounts to or is likely to amount to rupees fifty thousand or more for that year.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ) and sub-section ( 1A ), the following shall also`
  line `be deemed to be cases where taxable gifts chargeable to tax have escaped assessment, namely: —`
  line `( a ) where no return of taxable gifts has been furnished by the assessee although the taxable`
  line `gifts made by him or the taxable gifts made by any other person in respect of which he is`
  line `assessable under this Act during the previous year exceeded the maximum amount which is not`
  line `chargeable to gift-tax;`
  line `( b ) where return of taxable gifts has been furnished by the assessee but no assessment has`
  line `been made and it is noticed by the Assessing Officer that the assessee has understated the amount`
  line `or value of the taxable gifts or has claimed excessive exemption or deduction in the return.`
  line `( 1B ) ( a ) In a case where an assessment under sub-section ( 3 ) of section 15 or sub-section ( 1 ) of this`
  line `section has been made for the relevant assessment year, no notice shall be issued under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) 1 [by an Assessing Officer, who is below the rank of 2 [Assistant Commissioner or Deputy`
  line `Commissioner], unless the 3 [Joint Commissioner] is satisfied on the reasons recorded by such Assessing`
  line `Officer that it is a fit case for the issue of such notice]:`
  line `Provided that, after the expiry of four years from the end of the relevant assessment year, no such`
  line `notice shall be issued unless the Chief Commissioner or Commissioner is satisfied, on the reasons`
  line `recorded by the Assessing Officer aforesaid, that it is a fit case for the issue of such notice.`
  line `( b ) In a case, other than a case falling under clause ( a ), no notice shall be issued under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) by an Assessing Officer, who is below the rank of 3 [Joint Commissioner], after the`
  line `expiry of four years from the end of the relevant assessment year, unless the 3 [Joint Commissioner], is`
  line `satisfied, on the reasons recorded by such Assessing Officer, that it is a fit case for the issue of such`
  line notice.]
  line `( 2 ) Nothing contained in this section limiting the time within which any proceedings for assessment`
  line `or reassessment may be commenced shall apply to an assessment or reassessment to be made on the`
  line `assessee or any person in consequence of or to give effect to any finding or direction contained in an`
  line `order under section 22, section 23, section 24, section 26 or section 28 4 [or by a court in any proceedings`
  line `under any other law].`
  line `5 [ 16A. Time limit for completion of assessment and re-assessment. — 6 [( 1 ) No order of assessment`
  line `shall be made under section 15 at any time after the expiry of 7 [two years] from the end of the assessment`
  line `year in which the gifts were first assessable:`
  line `8 [Provided that, —`
  line `( a ) where the gifts were first assessable in the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 1987, or any earlier assessment year, such assessment may be made on or before the 31st day`
  line `of March, 1991;`
  line `( b ) where the gifts were first assessable in the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 1988, such assessment may be made on or before the 31st day of March, 1992.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 61, for “except by an Assessing Officer of the rank of Assistant Commissioner or Deputy`
  line `Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1990).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 76, for “Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 76, ibid., for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `4. Added by Act 4 of 1988, s. 171 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 112 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 172, for sub-section ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 13 of 1989, s. 31, for “one year” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
