  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-24
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Page 24`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  sourcePage 24
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line 24
  line `( 2 ) No order of assessment or re-assessment shall be made under section 16 after the expiry of two`
  line `years from the end of the financial year in which the notice under sub-section ( 1 ) of that section was`
  line `served:`
  line `Provided that, —`
  line `( i ) where the notice under clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 16 was served during the`
  line `financial year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1985, or the 1st day of April, 1986, such`
  line `assessment or re-assessment may be completed on or before the 31st day of March, 1990;`
  line `( ii ) where the notice under clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 16 relates to the assessment for`
  line `the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1985, or the 1st day of April, 1986, such`
  line `assessment or re-assessment may be completed on or before the 31st day of March, 1990, or the`
  line `expiry of two years from the end of the financial year in which such notice was served, whichever is`
  line later.
  line `Explanation. — References to section 16 in the proviso shall be construed as references to that section`
  line `as it stood before its amendment by the Direct Tax Laws (Amendment) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988).]`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ), an order of fresh assessment in`
  line `pursuance of an order passed on or after the 1st day of April, 1975, under section 22, section 23 or`
  line `section 24, setting aside or cancelling an assessment, may be made at any time before the expiry of 1 [two`
  line `years] from the end of the financial year in which the order under section 22 or section 23 is received by`
  line `the 2 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner] or, as the case may be, the order under section 24 is passed`
  line `by the Commissioner:`
  line `3 [Provided that where the order setting aside or cancelling the assessment was passed during the`
  line `financial year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1985, or the 1st day of April, 1986, the order of fresh`
  line `assessment may be made on or before the 31st day of March, 1990.]`
  line `( 4 ) The provisions of sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) shall not apply to the assessment or re-assessment made`
  line `on the assessee in consequence of, or to give effect to, any finding or direction contained in an order`
  line `under section 22, section 23, section 24, section 26 or section 28 or in an order of any court in a`
  line `proceeding otherwise than by way of appeal or reference under this Act and such assessment or re-`
  line `assessment may, subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 3 ), be completed at any time.`
  line `Explanation 1. — In computing the period of limitation for the purposes of this section —`
  line `( i ) the time taken in reopening the whole or any part of the proceeding or in giving an`
  line `opportunity to the assessee to be reheard under the proviso to section 38, or`
  line `( ii ) the period during which the assessment proceeding is stayed by an order or injunction of any`
  line court,
  line `shall be excluded:`
  line `4 [Provided that where immediately after the exclusion of the aforesaid time or period, the period of`
  line `limitation referred to in sub-sections ( 1 ), ( 2 ) and ( 3 ) available to the Assessing Officer for making an`
  line `order of assessment or re-assessment, as the case may be, is less than sixty days, such remaining period`
  line `shall be extended to sixty days and the aforesaid period of limitation shall be deemed to be extended`
  line accordingly.]
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 172, for “four years” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 161, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. The proviso ins. by s. 171, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. The proviso ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 87 (w.e.f. 27-9-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
