  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  sourcePage 25
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line 25
  line `Explanation 2. — Where, by an order referred to in sub-section ( 4 ), any gift is excluded from the`
  line `taxable gifts for an assessment year in respect of an assessee, then, an assessment of such gift for another`
  line `assessment year shall, for the purposes of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 16 and this section, be deemed to be`
  line `one made in consequence of, or to give effect to, any finding or direction contained in the said order.]`
  line `1 [16B. Interest for defaults in furnishing return of gifts. — ( 1 ) Where a return of gifts for any`
  line `assessment year under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 13 or section 14, or in response to a notice under`
  line `clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 4 ) of section 15, is furnished after the 30th day of June of such year, or is not`
  line `furnished, the assessee shall be liable to pay simple interest at the rate of two per cent. for every month or`
  line `part of a month comprised in the period commencing on the 1st day of July of the assessment year, and, —`
  line `( a ) where the return is furnished after the 30th day of June ending on the date of furnishing of the`
  line `return; or`
  line `( b ) where no return has been furnished, ending on the date of completion of the assessment under`
  line `sub-section ( 5 ) of section 15,`
  line `on the amount of tax payable on the taxable gifts as determined 2 [under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 15 or]`
  line `on regular assessment.`
  line `3 [ Explanation 1. — In this sub- section, “tax payable on the taxable gifts as determined under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 15” shall not include the additional gift -tax, if any, payable under section 15.]`
  line `Explanation 2. — Where in relation to an assessment year the assessment is made for the first time`
  line `under section 16, the assessment so made shall be regarded as a regular assessment for the purposes of`
  line `this section.`
  line `2 [ Explanation 3. — In this sub- section, “tax payable on the taxable gifts as determined under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 15 or on regular assessment” shall, for the purposes of computing the interest`
  line `payable under section 14B, be deemed to be tax payable on the taxable gifts as declared in the return.]`
  line `( 2 ) The interest payable under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be reduced by the interest, if any, paid under`
  line `section 14B towards the interest chargeable under this section.`
  line `( 3 ) Where the return of gifts for any assessment year, required by a notice under sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 16 issued 2 [after the determination of taxable gifts under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 15 or] after the`
  line `completion of an assessment under sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 5 ) of section 15 or section 16, is`
  line `furnished after the expiry of the time allowed under such notice, or is not furnished, the assessee shall be`
  line `liable to pay simple interest at the rate of two per cent. for every month or part of a month comprised in`
  line `the period commencing on the day immediately following the expiry of the time allowed as aforesaid,`
  line `and, —`
  line `( a ) where the return is furnished after the expiry of the time aforesaid, ending on the date of`
  line `furnishing the return; or`
  line `( b ) where no return has been furnished, ending on the date of completion of the re-assessment`
  line `under section 16,`
  line `on the amount by which the tax on the taxable gifts determined on the basis of such re-assessment`
  line `exceeds the tax on the taxable gifts as determined 2 [under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 15 or] on the basis of`
  line `the earlier assessment aforesaid.`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 173 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 85 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 85, ibid., for Explanation 1 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. The Explanation omitted by s. 85, ibid, (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
