  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  sourcePage 26
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line 26
  line `( 4 ) Where, as a result of an order under section 22 or section 23 or section 24 or section 26 or`
  line `section 28 or section 34, the amount of tax on which interest was payable under this section has been`
  line `increased or reduced, as the case may be, the interest shall be increased or reduced accordingly, and, —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the interest is increased, the Assessing Officer shall serve on the assessee a`
  line `notice of demand in the prescribed form specifying the sum payable, and such notice of demand shall`
  line `be deemed to be a notice under section 31 and the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly, and`
  line `( ii ) in a case where the interest is reduced, the excess interest paid, if any, shall be refunded.`
  line `( 5 ) The provisions of this section shall apply in respect of assessments for the assessment year`
  line `commencing on the 1st day of April, 1989 and subsequent assessment years.]`
  line `1 [17. Penalty for failure to furnish returns, to comply with notices and concealment of`
  line `gifts, etc. — ( 1 ) If the 2 [Assessing Officer], 3 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)], 4 [Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals),] 5 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner] or Appellate Tribunal, in the course of any`
  line `proceedings under this Act, is satisfied that any person —`
  line `6 * * * * *`
  line `( b ) has 7 *** failed to comply with a notice under sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-section ( 4 ) of section 15;`
  line or
  line `( c ) has concealed the particulars of any gift or deliberately furnished inaccurate particulars`
  line `thereof, he or it may, by order in writing, direct that such person shall pay by way of penalty —`
  line `8 * * * * *`
  line `9 [( ii ) in the cases referred to in clause ( b ), in addition to the amount of gift-tax payable by`
  line `him, a sum which shall not be less than one thousand rupees, but which may extend to`
  line `twenty-five thousand rupees for each such failure;]`
  line `( iii ) in the cases referred to in clause ( c ), in addition to any gift-tax payable by him, a sum`
  line `which shall not be less than twenty per cent. but which shall not exceed one and half times the`
  line `amount of the tax, if any, which would have been avoided if the return made by such person had`
  line `been accepted as correct:`
  line `10 [Provided that in the cases referred to in clause ( b ), no penalty shall be imposable if the person`
  line `proves that there was a reasonable cause for the failure referred to in that clause.]`
  line `11 [ Explanation. — Where any adjustment is made in the taxable gifts declared in the return under`
  line `the proviso to clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 15 and additional gift-tax charged under that`
  line `section, the provisions of this sub-section shall not apply in relation to the adjustments so made.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 14, for Section 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Gift - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 161, ibid., for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `6. Clause ( a ) omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 86 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `7. The words “without reasonable cause” omitted by Act 46 of 1986, s. 40 (w.e.f. 10 -9-1986).`
  line `8. Clause ( i ) omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 86 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `9. Subs. by s. 86, ibid., for clause ( ii ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `10. Subs. by s. 86, ibid., for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `11. Ins. by s. 86, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-27
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Page 27`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  sourcePage 27
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line 27
  line `( 2 ) No order imposing a penalty under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be made unless the assessee has been`
  line `heard or has been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line `1 [( 3 ) No order imposing a penalty under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be made, —`
  line `( i ) by the Income-tax Officer, where the penalty exceeds ten thousand rupees;`
  line `( ii ) by the 2 [Assistant Commissioner or Deputy Commissioner] where the penalty exceeds`
  line `twenty thousand rupees,`
  line `except with the prior approval of the 3 [Joint Commissioner.]`
  line `( 4 ) A 4 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)], 5 [a Commissioner (Appeals), a 6 [Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner] or the Appellate Tribunal] on making an order under this section imposing a penalty, shall`
  line `forthwith send a copy of the same to the 7 [Assessing Officer].]`
  line `8 [( 5 ) No order imposing a penalty under this section shall be passed —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the assessment to which the proceedings for imposition of penalty relate is the`
  line `subject-matter of an appeal to the Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or Commissioner (Appeals) under`
  line `section 22 or an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 23, after the expiry`
  line `of the financial year in which the proceedings, in the course of which action for the imposition of`
  line `penalty has been initiated, are completed, or six months from the end of the month in which the order`
  line `of the Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or the Commissioner (Appeals) or, as the case may be, the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal is received by the Chief Commissioner or Commissioner, whichever is later;`
  line `( ii ) in a case where the relevant assessment is the subject-matter of revision under sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 24, after the expiry of six months from the end of the month in which such order of revision`
  line `is passed;`
  line `( iii ) in any other case, after the expiry of the financial year in which the proceedings, in the`
  line `course of which action for the imposition of penalty has been initiated, are completed, or six months`
  line `from the end of the month in which action for imposition of penalty is initiated, whichever period`
  line `expires later.`
  line `Explanation. — In computing the period of limitation for the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) the time taken in giving an opportunity to the assessee to be reheard under the proviso to`
  line `section 38; and`
  line `( ii ) any period during which a proceeding under this section for the levy of penalty is stayed by`
  line `an order or injunction of any court,`
  line `shall be excluded.`
  line `( 6 ) The provisions of this section as they stood immediately before their amendment by the Direct`
  line `Tax Laws (Amendment) Act, 1989 (3 of 1989) shall apply to and in relation to any assessment for the`
  line `assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1988, or any earlier assessment year and references in`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 86, for sub-section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 76, for “Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 76, ibid., for “ Deputy Commissioner ” (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161 for “An Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161 for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 161, ibid., “ Gift- tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 86 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-28
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Page 28`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  sourcePage 28
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line 28
  line `this section to the other provisions of this Act shall be construed as references to those provisions as for`
  line `the time being in force and applicable to the relevant assessment year.]`
  line `1 [17A. Penalty for failure to answer questions, sign statements, furnish information, allow`
  line `inspections, etc. — ( 1 ) If a person, —`
  line `( a ) being legally bound to state the truth of any matter touching the subject of his assessment,`
  line `refuses to answer any question put to him by a gift-tax authority in the exercise of his powers under`
  line `this Act; or`
  line `( b ) refuses to sign any statement made by him in the course of any proceedings under this Act,`
  line `which a gift-tax authority may legally require him to sign; or`
  line `( c ) to whom a summons is issued under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 36, either to attend to give`
  line `evidence or produce books of account or other documents at a certain place and time, omits to attend`
  line `or produce the books of account or documents at the place and time,`
  line `he shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum which shall not be less than five hundred rupees but which may`
  line `extend to ten thousand rupees for each such default or failure:`
  line `Provided that no penalty shall be imposable under clause ( c ) if the person proves that there was`
  line `reasonable cause for the said failure.`
  line `( 2 ) If a person fails to furnish in due time any statement or information which such person is bound to`
  line `furnish to the Assessing Officer under section 37, he shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum which shall not`
  line `be less than one hundred rupees but which may extend to two hundred rupees for every day during which`
  line `the failure continues:`
  line `Provided that no penalty shall be imposable under this sub-section if the person proves that there was`
  line `reasonable cause for the said failure.`
  line `( 3 ) Any penalty imposable under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) shall be imposed —`
  line `( a ) in a case where the contravention, failure or default in respect of which such penalty is`
  line `imposable occurs in the course of any proceeding before a gift-tax authority not lower in rank than a`
  line `2 [Joint Director] or a 3 [Joint Commissioner], by such gift-tax authority;`
  line `( b ) in any other case, by the 2 [Joint Director] or the 3 [Joint Commissioner].`
  line `( 4 ) No order under this section shall be passed by any gift-tax authority referred to in sub-section ( 3 )`
  line `unless the person on whom penalty is proposed to be imposed has been heard or has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter by such authority.`
  line `Explanation. —In this section, “gift - tax authority” includes a Director General, Director, 2 [Joint`
  line `Director], 4 [Assistant Director or Deputy Director] or Valuation Officer while exercising the powers`
  line `vested in a court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), when trying a suit in respect of the`
  line `matters specified in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 36.]`
  line `5 [18. Rebate on advance payments. — If a person making a taxable gift pays into the treasury`
  line `within fifteen days of his making the gift any part of the amount of tax due on the gift calculated at rates`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 87, for section 17A (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 76, for “Deputy Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 76, ibid., for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 76, ibid., for “Assistant Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 115, for section 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
