obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line 29
  line `specified in the Schedule 1 [or at the rate specified in sub-section ( 2 ) of section 3], he shall, at the time of`
  line `assessment under section 15, be given credit —`
  line `( i ) for the amount so paid; and`
  line `( ii ) for a sum equal to one-ninth of the amount so paid, so however, that such sum shall in no`
  line `case exceed one-tenth of the tax due on the gift.`
  line `Explanation. — If a person makes more than one taxable gift in the course of a previous year, the`
  line `amount of tax due on any one of such gifts shall be the difference between the total amount of tax due on`
  line `the aggregate value of all the taxable gifts so far made, including the taxable gift in respect of which tax`
  line `has to be paid, calculated at the rates specified in the Schedule or, as the case may be 2 [at the rate`
  line `specified in sub-section ( 2 ) of section 3], and the total amount of tax on the aggregate value of all the gifts`
  line `made during that year, excluding the taxable gift in respect of which tax has to be paid, calculated at the`
  line `rates specified in the Schedule or, as the case may be, 2 [at the rate specified in sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 3].]`
  line `3 [ 18A. Credit for stamp duty paid on instrument of gift. — Where any stamp duty has been paid`
  line `under any law relating to stamp duty in force in any State on an instrument of gift of property, the`
  line `assessee shall be entitled to a deduction from the gift-tax payable by him of an amount equal to the stamp`
  line `duty so paid or one-half of the gift-tax payable, before making the deduction under this section,`
  line `whichever is less.]`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `CHAPTER V`
  line `L IABILITY TO ASSESSMENT IN SPECIAL CASES`
  line `19. Tax of deceased person payable by legal representative. — ( 1 ) Where a person dies, his`
  line `executor, administrator or other legal representative shall be liable to pay out of the estate of the deceased`
  line `person, to the extent to which the estate is capable of meeting the charge, the gift-tax determined as`
  line `payable by such person, or any sum which would have been payable by him under this Act if he had not`
  line died.
  line `( 2 ) Where a person dies without having furnished a return under section 13, or after having furnished`
  line `a return which the 5 [Assessing Officer] has reason to believe to be incorrect or incomplete, the`
  line `5 [Assessing Officer] may make an assessment of the value of the taxable gifts made by such person and`
  line `determine the gift-tax payable by him, and for this purpose may, by the issue of the appropriate notice`
  line `which would have had to be served upon the deceased person if he had survived, require from the`
  line `executor, administrator, or other legal representative of the deceased person any accounts, documents, or`
  line `other evidence which might, under the provisions of section 15, have been required from the deceased`
  line person.
  line `( 3 ) The provisions of sections 13, 14 and 16 shall apply to an executor, administrator or other legal`
  line `representative as they apply to any person referred to in 6 [those sections].`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 1986, s. 44, for “or, in case where the provisions of Section 6 -A are applicable to a gift, in the manner`
  line `specified in that section” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1987).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 44, ibid., for “in the manner specified in section 6A” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1987).`
  line `3. Subs, by Act 14 of 1982, s. 39 for section 18A (w.e.f. 1-4-1983).`
  line `4. Chapter IV-A containing section 18- B” omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989). Earlier it was inserted by Act 4 of`
  line `1988, s. 175 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Gift - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 58 of 1960, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for “that section” (w.e.f. 26 -12-1960).`
