  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  sourcePage 30
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line 30
  line `1 [ 19A. Assessment of persons leaving India. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in section`
  line `3, when it appears to the 2 [Assessing Officer] that any individual may leave India during the current`
  line `assessment year, or shortly after its expiry and that he has no present intention of returning to India, the`
  line `gifts made by such individual during the period from the expiry of the previous year for that assessment`
  line `year up to the probable date of his departure from India, shall be chargeable to gift-tax in that assessment`
  line year.
  line `( 2 ) The taxable gifts made in each completed previous year or part of any previous year included in`
  line `such period shall be chargeable to gift-tax at the rate or rates specified in the Schedule 3 [or, as the case`
  line `may be, at the rate specified in sub-section ( 2 ) of section 3], and separate assessment shall be made in`
  line `respect of each such completed previous year or part of any previous year.`
  line `( 3 ) The 2 [Assessing Officer] may estimate the value of the gifts made by such individual during such`
  line `period or any part thereof, where it cannot be readily determined in the manner provided in this Act.`
  line `( 4 ) For the purpose of making an assessment under sub-section ( 1 ), the 2 [Assessing Officer] may`
  line `serve a notice upon such individual requiring him to furnish, within such time, not being less than seven`
  line `days, as may be specified in the notice, a return in the same form and verified in the same manner as`
  line `4 [a return under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 13], giving particulars of the gifts made by him during each`
  line `completed previous year comprised in the period referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) and during any part of the`
  line `previous year comprised in that period; and the provisions of this Act shall, so far as may be, and subject`
  line `to the provisions of this section, apply 5 [as if the notice were a notice issued under clause ( i ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 4 ) of section 15].`
  line `( 5 ) The gift-tax chargeable under this section shall be in addition to the tax, if any, chargeable under`
  line `any other provision of this Act.`
  line `( 6 ) Where the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) are applicable, any notice issued by the 2 [Assessing`
  line `Officer] under 6 [clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 4 ) of section 15] or under section 16 in respect of any gift-tax`
  line `chargeable under any other provisions of this Act may, notwithstanding anything contained in 6 [clause ( i )`
  line `of sub-section ( 4 ) of section 15], or section 16, as the case may be, require the furnishing of the return by`
  line `such individual within such period, not being less than seven days, as the 2 [Assessing Officer] may think`
  line proper.]
  line `20. Assessment after partition of a Hindu undivided family. — ( 1 ) Where, at the time of making`
  line `an assessment, it is brought to the notice of the 2 [Assessing Officer] that a partition has taken place among`
  line `the members of a Hindu undivided family, and the 2 [Assessing Officer], after enquiry, is satisfied that the`
  line `joint family property has been partitioned among the various members or groups of members in definite`
  line `portions, he shall record an order to that effect and he shall make assessments 7 [on the value of the taxable`
  line `gifts] made by the family as such as if no partition had taken place and each member or group of members`
  line `shall be liable jointly and severally for the tax assessed on the value of the taxable gifts made by the joint`
  line `family as such.`
  line `( 2 ) Where the 2 [Assessing Officer] is not so satisfied, he may, by order, declare that such family shall`
  line `be deemed for the purposes of this Act to continue to be a Hindu undivided family.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Gift - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 1986, s. 45 (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 186, for “a return under sub -section ( 2 ) of section 13” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 186, ibid., for “as if the notice were a notice issued under sub -section ( 2 ) of section 13” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 186, ibid., for “sub -section ( 2 ) of section 13” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 58 of 1960, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for “on the amount of taxable gifts” (w.e.f. 26 -12-1960).`
