obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line 31
  line `21. Liability in case of discontinued firm or association of persons. — ( 1 ) Where a firm or`
  line `association of persons liable to pay gift-tax has been discontinued or dissolved, the 1 [Assessing Officer]`
  line `shall determine the gift-tax payable by the firm or association of persons as such as if no such`
  line `discontinuance or dissolution had taken place.`
  line `(2) If the 1 [Assessing Officer], the 2 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)], 3 [the Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals)] or the Appellate Tribunal in the course of any proceeding under this Act in respect of any such`
  line `firm or other association of persons as is referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) is satisfied that the firm or`
  line `association is guilty of any of the acts specified in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 17, he or it may impose or direct the imposition of a penalty in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of that section.`
  line `(3) Every person who was at the time of such discontinuance or dissolution a partner of the firm or a`
  line `member of the association, as the case may be, shall be jointly and severally liable for the amount of tax`
  line `or penalty payable, and all the provisions of Chapter VII, so far as may be, shall apply to any such`
  line `assessment or imposition of penalty.`
  line `4 [21A. Assessment of donee when the donor cannot be found. — ( 1 ) Where an 1 [Assessing`
  line `Officer] after using all due and reasonable diligence cannot find the donor who had made any taxable`
  line `gifts, for the purpose of service of notice under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 13 or under section 16, the`
  line `1 [Assessing Officer] may make an assessment of the value of all such taxable gifts made by him and`
  line `determine the gift-tax payable by him and for this purpose may, by the issue of the appropriate notice`
  line `which would have had to be served upon the donor, require from the donee or donees any accounts,`
  line `documents or other evidence which might, under the provisions of section 15, have been required from`
  line `the donor.`
  line `( 2 ) Where any assessment in respect of the taxable gifts made by the donor has been made under sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ), every donee shall be liable for the gift-tax so assessed:`
  line `Provided that where the donees are more than one, they shall be jointly and severally liable for the`
  line `amount of the gift-tax so assessed:`
  line `Provided further that the amount of the gift-tax which may be recovered from each donee shall not`
  line `exceed the value of the gift made to him as on the date of the gift.`
  line `(3) The provisions of sections 13, 14 and 16 shall apply to a donee as they apply to any person`
  line `referred to in those sections.]`
  line `CHAPTER VI`
  line `A PPEALS, REVISIONS AND REFERENCES`
  line `22. Appeal to the 2 [ Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] from orders of 1 [Assessing Officer]. —`
  line `( 1 ) 5 [Subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 1A ), any person,] —`
  line `( a ) objecting to the value of 6 * * * taxable gifts determined under this Act; or`
  line `( b ) objecting to the amount of gift-tax determined as payable by him under this Act; or`
  line `( c ) denying his liability to be assessed under this Act; or`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Gift - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 161, ibid., for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule, for “Any person” (w.e.f. 10 -7-1978).`
  line `6. The word “ his ” omitted by Act 53 of 1962, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
