obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line 32
  line `1 [( d ) objecting to any penalty imposed by the Assessing Officer under section 17 2 * * *]; or`
  line `( e ) objecting to any order of the 3 [Assessing Officer] under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 20; or`
  line `( f ) objecting to any penalty imposed by the 3 [Assessing Officer] under 4 [sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 221 of the Income-tax Act] as applied under section 33 for the purposes of gift-tax; 5 [or]`
  line `6 [( g ) objecting to an order of the 3 [Assessing Officer] under section 34 having the effect of`
  line `enhancing the assessment or reducing a refund or an order refusing to allow the claim made by the`
  line `assessee under that section; or`
  line `7 * * * * *]`
  line `may appeal to the 8 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] against the assessment or order, as the case may be,`
  line `in the prescribed form and verified in the prescribed manner:`
  line `Provided that no appeal shall lie under clause ( f ) unless the tax has been paid before the appeal is`
  line filed.
  line `9 [( 1A ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), any person, —`
  line `( a ) objecting to the value of taxable gifts determined under this Act or objecting to the amount of`
  line `gift-tax determined as payable by him or denying his liability to be assessed under this Act where the`
  line `value of taxable gifts determined on assessment exceeds two lakh rupees; or`
  line `10 [( b ) objecting to any assessment or order referred to in clauses ( a ) to ( g ) (both inclusive) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ), where such assessment or order has been made by the 11 [Joint Commissioner] in`
  line `exercise of the powers or functions conferred on or assigned to him under section 7 or section 10; or`
  line `12 [( c ) objecting to any penalty imposed under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 17 with the previous`
  line `approval of the 11 [Joint Commissioner] as specified in sub-section (3) of that section;]`
  line `( d ) objecting to any penalty imposed by the 13 [Joint Director] or the 11 [Joint Commissioner]`
  line `under section 17A; or]`
  line `( e ) objecting to any order made by an 3 [Assessing Officer] in the case of such persons or classes`
  line `of persons as the Board may, having regard to the nature of the cases, the complexities involved and`
  line `other relevant considerations, direct,`
  line `may appeal to the Commissioner (Appeals) against the assessment or order, as the case may be, in the`
  line `prescribed form and verified in the prescribed manner:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 176, for clause ( d ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. The words, figures, letters and bracket “as it stood immediately before the 1st day of April, 1989 or under section 17 as`
  line `amended by the Direct Tax Laws (Amendment) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988) ” omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 88 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Gift –tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 17, for “sub -section ( 1 ) of section 46 of the Income- tax Act” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1963).`
  line `5. Added by s. 17, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `6. Ins. by s. 17, ibid, (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `7. Clause ( h ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 176 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 161, ibid., for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 176, for clauses ( b ), ( c ) and ( d ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 76, for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `12. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 88, for clause ( c ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `13. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 76, for “Deputy Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
