obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line 33
  line `Provided that no appeal shall lie under clause ( b ) of this sub-section against any order referred to in`
  line `clause ( f ) of sub-section ( 1 ) unless the tax has been paid before the appeal is filed.]`
  line `1 [( 1B ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), the Board or the Director General or`
  line `the Chief Commissioner or the Commissioner, if so authorised by the Board, may, by order in writing,`
  line `transfer any appeal which is pending before a Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) and any matter arising out`
  line `of or connected with such appeal and which is so pending, to the Commissioner (Appeals), if the Board`
  line `or, as the case may be, the Director General, the Chief Commissioner or the Commissioner (at the request`
  line `of the appellant or otherwise) is satisfied that it is necessary or expedient so to do having regard to the`
  line `nature of the case, the complexities involved and other relevant considerations and the Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals) may proceed with such appeal or matter from the stage at which it was before it was so`
  line `transferred:`
  line `Provided that the appellant may demand that before proceeding further with the appeal or matter, the`
  line `previous proceeding or any part thereof be reopened or that he be reheard.]]`
  line `( 2 ) An appeal shall be presented within thirty days of the receipt of the notice of demand relating to`
  line `the assessment or penalty objected to, or the date on which any order objected to, is communicated to`
  line `him, but the 2 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 3 [or, as the case may be, the Commissioner (Appeals)]`
  line `may admit an appeal after the expiration of the period aforesaid if he is satisfied that the appellant had`
  line `sufficient cause for not presenting the appeal within that period.`
  line `( 3 ) The 2 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 3 [or, as the case may be, the Commissioner (Appeals)]`
  line `shall fix a day and place for the hearing of the appeal and may from time to time adjourn the hearing.`
  line `( 4 ) The 2 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 3 [or, as the case may be, the Commissioner (Appeals)]`
  line `may, —`
  line `( a ) at the hearing of an appeal allow an appellant to go into any ground of appeal not specified in`
  line `the grounds of appeal;`
  line `( b ) before disposing of an appeal, make such further inquiry as he thinks fit or cause further`
  line `enquiry to be made by the 4 [Assessing Officer].`
  line `( 5 ) In disposing of an appeal, the 2 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 3 [or, as the case may be, the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals)] may pass such order as he thinks fit which may include an order enhancing the`
  line `amount of gift-tax determined or penalty imposed:`
  line `Provided that no order enhancing the amount of gift-tax determined or penalty imposed shall be made`
  line `unless the person affected thereby has been given a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against such`
  line enhancement.
  line `5 [( 5A ) In disposing of an appeal, the 2 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 3 [or, as the case may be, the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals)] may consider and decide any matter arising out of the proceedings in which the`
  line `order appealed against was passed, notwithstanding that such matter was not raised before the 2 [Deputy`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals)] 3 [or, as the case may be, the Commissioner (Appeals)] by the appellant.`
  line `( 5B ) The order of the 2 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 3 [or, as the case may be, the Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals)] disposing of the appeal shall be in writing and shall state the points for determination, the`
  line `decision thereon and the reasons for the decision.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 176, for “ sub-sections ( 1B ) and ( 1C ) ” (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 161, ibid., for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Gift - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
