obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line 34
  line `( 6 ) A copy of every order passed by the 1 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 2 [or, as the case may be,`
  line `the Commissioner (Appeals)] under this section shall be forwarded to the appellant and the 3 [Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner.]`
  line `22A. [ Application by the assessee in certain cases. ] — Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 1989 (3 of 1989), s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Which was inserted by the Direct Tax Laws (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 1987 (4 of 1988), s. 177 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989 ).`
  line `23. Appeal to the Appellate Tribunal. — 4 [( 1 ) An assessee, objecting to an order passed by the`
  line `1 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 5 [or the Commissioner (Appeals)] 6 [under section 17 or section 17A]`
  line `or section 22 7 * * *] or sub-section ( 2 ) of section 36 8 * * *, may appeal to the Appellate Tribunal within`
  line `sixty days of the date on which the order is communicated to him.]`
  line `( 2 ) The Commissioner may, if he is not satisfied as to the correctness of any order passed by a`
  line `1 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 5 [or a Commissioner (Appeals)] under section 22, direct the`
  line `9 [Assessing Officer] to appeal to the Appellate Tribunal against such order, and such appeal may be made`
  line `at any time before the expiry of sixty days of the date on which the order is communicated to the`
  line Commissioner.
  line `10 [( 2A ) The 9 [Assessing Officer] or the assessee, as the case may be, on receipt of the notice that an`
  line `appeal against the order of the 1 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 5 [or the Commissioner (Appeals)] has`
  line `been preferred under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) by the other party, may, notwithstanding that he`
  line `may not have appealed against such order or any part thereof, within thirty days of the receipt of the`
  line `notice, file a memorandum of cross-objections, verified in the prescribed manner, against any part of the`
  line `order of the 1 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 5 [or the Commissioner (Appeals)], and such`
  line `memorandum shall be disposed of by the Appellate Tribunal as if it were an appeal presented within the`
  line `time specified in sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ).]`
  line `11 [( 3 ) The Appellate Tribunal may admit an appeal or permit the filing of a memorandum of`
  line `cross-objections after the expiry of the relevant period referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) or`
  line `sub-section ( 2A ), if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not presenting it within that period.]`
  line `( 4 ) An appeal to the Appellate Tribunal shall be in the prescribed form and shall be verified in the`
  line `prescribed manner and shall, except in the case of an appeal referred to in sub-section ( 2 ), be`
  line `accompanied by a fee of 12 [two hundred rupees].`
  line `( 5 ) The Appellate Tribunal may, after giving the parties to the appeal an opportunity of being heard,`
  line `pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit, and any such orders may include an order enhancing the amount`
  line `of gift-tax determined or penalty imposed:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 18, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 116, for “under section 17” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1976).`
  line `7. The words, figure and letters “or section 22A” omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989). Earlier inserted by Act 4 of`
  line `1988, s. 186 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `8. The Words “or to an order passed by the Inspecting Assistant Commissioner under section 17A” omitted by Act 29 of 1977,`
  line `s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Gift - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `11. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for sub-section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `12. Sub s. by Act 16 of 1981, for “one hundred and twenty - five rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1981).`
