  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  sourcePage 35
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line 35
  line `Provided that no order enhancing the amount of gift-tax determined or penalty imposed shall be made`
  line `unless the person affected thereby has been given a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against such`
  line enhancement.
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `( 9 ) A copy of every order passed by the Appellate Tribunal under this section shall be forwarded to`
  line `the assessee and the Commissioner.`
  line `( 10 ) Save as provided in section 26, any order passed by the Appellate Tribunal on appeal shall be`
  line final.
  line `( 11 ) The provisions of 4 [sub-sections ( 1 ), ( 4 ) and ( 5 ) of section 255] of the Income-tax Act shall`
  line `apply to the Appellate Tribunal in the discharge of its functions under this Act as they apply to it in the`
  line `discharge of its functions under the Income-tax Act.`
  line `24. Powers of Commissioner to revise orders of subordinate authorities. — ( 1 ) The`
  line `Commissioner may, either on his own motion or on application made by an assessee in this behalf, call`
  line `for the record of any proceeding under this Act in which an order has been passed by any authority`
  line `subordinate to him, and may make such inquiry, or cause such inquiry to be made, and subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Act, pass such order thereon, not being an order prejudicial to the assessee, as the`
  line `Commissioner thinks fit:`
  line `Provided that the Commissioner shall not revise any order under this sub-section in any case —`
  line `( a ) where an appeal against the order lies to the 5 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 6 [or to the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals)] or to the Appellate Tribunal and the time within which such appeal can be`
  line `made has not expired or, 7 [in the case of an appeal to the Commissioner (Appeals) or to the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal], the assessee has not waived his right of appeal;`
  line `( b ) where the order is pending in appeal before the 5 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] or has`
  line `been the subject of an appeal 6 [to the Commissioner (Appeals) or] to the Appellate Tribunal;`
  line `( c ) where the application is made by the assessee for such revision unless —`
  line `( i ) the application is accompanied by a fee of rupees twenty-five; and`
  line `( ii ) the application is made within one year from the date of the order sought to be revised or`
  line `within such further period as the Commissioner may think fit to allow on being satisfied that the`
  line `assessee was prevented by sufficient cause from making the application within that period; and`
  line `( d ) where the order is sought to be revised by the Commissioner of his own motion, if such order`
  line `is made more than one year previously.`
  line `1. Sub-section (6) omitted by Act 45 of 1972, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-1-1973).`
  line `2. Sub-section ( 7 ) omitted by s. 22, ibid, (w.e.f. 1-1-1973).`
  line `3. Sub-section ( 8 ) omitted by s. 22, ibid, (w.e.f. 1-1-1973).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 18, for “sub -sections ( 5 ), ( 7 ) and ( 8 ) of section 5- A” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1963).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 of the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 39 ibid., of the Fifth Schedule, “in the case of the Appellate Tribunal” (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
