  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  sourcePage 36
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line 36
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, —`
  line `( a ) the 1 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] shall be deemed to be an authority subordinate to`
  line `the Commissioner; and`
  line `( b ) an order by the Commissioner declining to interfere shall be deemed not to be an order`
  line `prejudicial to the assessee.`
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section ( 1 ), the Commissioner may call for`
  line `and examine the record of any proceeding under this Act, and, if he considers that any order passed`
  line `therein by an 2 [Assessing Officer] is erroneous in so far as it is prejudicial to the interests of revenue, he`
  line `may, after giving the assessee an opportunity of being heard, and after making or causing to be made such`
  line `inquiry as he deems necessary, pass such order thereon as the circumstances of the case justify, including`
  line `an order enhancing or modifying the assessment or cancelling it and directing a fresh assessment.`
  line `3 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that, for the purposes of this`
  line `sub-section, —`
  line `( a ) an order passed 4 [on or before or after the 1st day of June, 1988] by the Assessing Officer`
  line `shall include an order passed by the 5 [Joint Commissioner] in exercise of the powers or in`
  line `performance of the functions of an Assessing Officer conferred on or assigned to him under orders or`
  line `directions issued by the Board or by the Chief Commissioner or Director General or Commissioner`
  line `authorised by the Board in this behalf under section 120 of the Income-tax Act read with section 7 of`
  line `this Act;`
  line `( b ) “record” 6 [shall include and shall be deemed always to have included] all records relating to`
  line `any proceeding under this Act available at the time of examination by the Commissioner;`
  line `( c ) where any order referred to in this sub-section and passed by the Assessing Officer had been`
  line `the subject matter of any appeal, 4 [filed on or before or after the 1st day of June, 1988], the powers of`
  line `the Commissioner under this sub-section shall extend 4 [and shall be deemed always to have extended]`
  line `to such matters as had not been considered and decided in such appeal.]`
  line `( 3 ) No order shall be made under sub-section ( 2 ) after the expiry of two years 7 [from the end of the`
  line `financial year in which the order sought to be revised was passed.]`
  line `8 [ Explanation. — In computing the period of limitation for purposes of this sub-section, the time taken`
  line `in giving an opportunity to the assessee to be reheard under the proviso to section 38 and any period`
  line `during which any proceeding under this section is stayed by an order or injunction of any court shall be`
  line excluded.]
  line `25. Appeal to the Appellate Tribunal from orders of enhancement by 9 [Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner]. — 10 [( 1 ) An assessee objecting to an order passed by the 9 [Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner] 11 [under section 17 or section 17A] or to an order of enhancement passed by him under`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 161, ibid., for “ Gift-tax Officer ” ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 68, for Explanation (w.e.f. 1-6-1988).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 13 of 1989, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-6-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 76, for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 13 of 1989, s. 32, for “includes” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1988).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 74, for “form the date of the order sought to be revised” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1984).`
  line `8. Explanation added by Act 53 of 1962, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 117, for “under Section 17” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1976).`
