obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line 39
  line `( iv ) in relation to the Union territory of Andaman and Nicobar Islands, the High Court of`
  line Calcutta;
  line `( v ) in relation to the Union territory of 1 [Lakshadweep], the High Court of Kerala;]`
  line `2 [( va ) in relation to the Union territory of Chandigarh, the High Court of Punjab and Haryana;]`
  line `3 [( vi ) in relation to the Union territories of Dadra and Nagar Haveli and Goa, Daman and Diu, the`
  line `High Court at Bombay;`
  line `( vii ) in relation to the Union territory of Pondicherry, the High Court at Madras.]`
  line `CHAPTER VII`
  line `P AYMENT AND RECOVERY OF GIFT-TAX`
  line `4 [29. Gift-tax by whom payable. — Subject to the provisions of this Act, gift-tax shall be payable`
  line `by the donor but when in the opinion of the 5 [Assessing Officer] the tax cannot be recovered from the`
  line `donor, it may be recovered from the donee:`
  line `Provided that where the donees are more than one, they shall be jointly and severally liable for the`
  line `amount of tax determined to be payable by the donor:`
  line `Provided further that the amount of tax which may be recovered from each donee shall not exceed the`
  line `value of the gift made to him as on the date of the gift.]`
  line `30. Gift-tax to be charged on property gifted. — Gift-tax payable in respect of any gift comprising`
  line `immovable property shall be a first charge on that property but any such charge shall not affect the title of`
  line `a bona fide purchaser for valuable consideration without notice of the charge.`
  line `6 [ 31 Notice of demand. — When any tax, interest, penalty, fine or any other sum is payable in`
  line `consequence of any order passed under this Act, the 5 [Assessing Officer] shall serve upon the assessee a`
  line `notice of demand in the prescribed form specifying the sum so payable.]`
  line `32. Recovery of tax and penalties. — ( 1 ) Any amount specified as payable in a notice of demand`
  line `under section 31 shall be paid within 7 [thirty days] of the service of the notice at the place and to the`
  line `person mentioned in the notice:`
  line `Provided that, where the 2 [Assessing Officer] has any reason to believe that it will be detrimental to`
  line `revenue if the full period of 7 [thirty days] aforesaid is allowed, he may, with the previous approval of the`
  line `8 [ 9 [Joint] Commissioner], direct that the sum specified in the notice of demand shall be paid within such`
  line `period being a period less than the period of 7 [thirty days] aforesaid, as may be specified by him in the`
  line `notice of demand.`
  line `1. Subs. by the Laccadive, Minicoy and Amindivi Islands (Alteration of Name) Adaptation of Laws Order, 1974, for “the`
  line `Laccadive, Minicoy and Amindivi Islands” (w.r.e.f. 1 -11-1973).`
  line `2. Ins. by the Punjab Reorganisation and Delhi High Court (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1968`
  line `(w.r.e.f. 1-11-1966).`
  line `3. Ins. by the Taxation Laws (Extension to Union Territories) Regulation, 1963 (3 of 1963), s. 3 and the Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Gift - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 24, for Section 31, 32 and 33 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 178, for “thirty - five days” (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 161, ibid, for “Inspecting Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 76, for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-40
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Page 40`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  sourcePage 40
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line 40
  line `( 2 ) If the amount specified in any notice of demand under section 31 is not paid within the period`
  line `limited under sub-section ( 1 ), the assessee shall be liable to pay simple interest at 1 [one and one-half per`
  line `cent. for every month or part of a month comprised in the period commencing from the day immediately`
  line `following the end of the period mentioned in sub-section ( 1 ) and ending with the day on which the`
  line `amount is paid]:`
  line `2 [Provided that where as a result of an order under section 22, or section 23, or section 24, or`
  line `section 25, or section 26, or section 28, or section 34, the amount on which interest was payable under`
  line `this section had been reduced, the interest shall be reduced accordingly and the excess interest paid, if`
  line `any, shall be refunded:]`
  line `3 [Provided further that in respect of any period commencing on or before the 31st day of March, 1989`
  line `and ending after that date, such interest shall, in respect of so much of such period as falls after that date,`
  line `be calculated at the rate of one and one-half per cent. for every month or part of a month.]`
  line `( 3 ) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section ( 2 ), on an application made by the`
  line `assessee before the expiry of the due date under sub-section ( 1 ), the 4 [Assessing Officer] may extend the`
  line `time for payment or allow payment by instalments subject to such conditions as he may think fit to`
  line `impose in the circumstances of the case.`
  line `( 4 ) If the amount is not paid within the time limited under sub-section ( 1 ) or extended under`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ), as the case may be, at the place and to the person mentioned in the said notice, the`
  line `assessee shall be deemed to be in default.`
  line `(5) If, in a case where payment by instalments is allowed under sub-section ( 3 ), the assessee commits`
  line `default in paying any one of the instalments within the time fixed under that sub-section, the assessee`
  line `shall be deemed to be in default as to the whole of the amount then outstanding, and the other instalment`
  line `or instalments shall be deemed to have been due on the same date as the instalment actually in default.`
  line `( 6 ) Where the assessee has presented an appeal under section 22, the 4 [Assessing Officer] may in his`
  line `discretion and subject to such conditions as he may think fit to impose in the circumstances of the case,`
  line `treat the assessee as not being in default in respect of the amount in dispute in the appeal, even though the`
  line `time for payment has expired as long as such appeal remains undisposed of.]`
  line `33. Mode of recovery. — The provisions contained in 5 [sections 221 to 227, 228A,] 229, 231 and`
  line `232 of the Income-tax Act and the Second and Third Schedules to that Act and any rules made thereunder`
  line `shall, so far as may be, apply as if the said provisions were provisions of this Act and referred to gift-tax`
  line `and sums imposed by way of penalty, fine and interest under this Act instead of to income-tax and sums`
  line `imposed by way of penalty, fine and interest under that Act 6 [and to the corresponding gift-tax authorities`
  line `instead of to the income-tax authorities specified therein].`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 178, for “fifteen per cent. annum from th e day commencing after the end of the period`
  line `mentioned in sub-section ( 1 )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `2. The proviso added by Act 5 of 1964, s. 52 (1-4-1963).`
  line `3. The proviso ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 178 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 161, ibid., for “Gift - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 53, for “sections 221 to 227” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1972).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 179, for “Gift -tax Officer and Commissioner of Gift-tax instead of to Income tax Officer and`
  line `Commissioner of Income- tax” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
