obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line 41
  line `Explanation I. — Any reference to sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-section ( 6 ) of section 220 of the`
  line `Income-tax Act in the said provisions of that Act or the rules made thereunder shall be construed as`
  line `references to sub-sections ( 2 ) and ( 6 ) respectively of section 32 of this Act.`
  line `1 [ Explanation II. — The Chief Commissioner or Commissioner and the Tax Recovery Officer`
  line `referred to in the Income-tax Act shall be deemed to be the corresponding gift-tax authorities for the`
  line `purpose of recovery of gift-tax and sums imposed by way of penalty, fine and interest under this`
  line Act].]
  line `2 [CHAPTER VIIA`
  line `R EFUNDS`
  line `33A. Refunds. — ( 1 ) Where, as a result of any order passed in appeal or other proceeding under`
  line `this Act, refund of any amount becomes due to the assessee, the 3 [Assessing Officer] shall, except as`
  line `otherwise provided in this Act, refund the amount to the assessee without his having to make any`
  line `claim in that behalf:`
  line `4 [Provided that where, by the order aforesaid, —`
  line `( a ) an assessment is set aside or cancelled and an order of fresh assessment is directed to be`
  line `made, the refund, if any, shall become due only on the making of such fresh assessment;`
  line `( b ) the assessment is annulled, the refund shall become due only of the amount, if any, of the`
  line `tax paid in excess of the tax chargeable on the 5 [taxable gifts] returned by the assessee.]`
  line `6 [( 2 ) Where refund of any amount becomes due to the assessee as a result of an order under this`
  line `Act or under the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 15 after a return has been made under`
  line `section 13 or section 14 or in response to a notice under clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 4 ) of section 15 and`
  line `the Assessing Officer is of the opinion, having regard to the fact that, —`
  line `( i ) a notice has been issued, or is likely to be issued, under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 15 in`
  line `respect of the said return; or`
  line `( ii ) the order is the subject-matter of an appeal or further proceeding; or`
  line `( iii ) any other proceeding under this Act is pending,`
  line `that the grant of the refund is likely to adversely affect the revenue, the 3 [Assessing Officer] may, with the`
  line `previous approval of the Chief Commissioner or Commissioner, withhold the refund till such time as the`
  line `Chief Commissioner or Commissioner may determine.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988 s. 179, for “ Explanation II ” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Gift - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. The proviso added by Act 4 of 1988, s. 180 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 90, for “total income” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 36 of 1989, s. 33, for sub-section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
