obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line 42
  line `( 3 ) Where a refund is due to the assessee in pursuance of an order referred to in sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `and the 1 [Assessing Officer] does not grant the refund within a period of six months from the date of`
  line `such order, the Central Government shall pay to the assessee simple interest at 2 [fifteen per cent.] per`
  line `annum on the amount of refund due from the date immediately following the expiry of the period of`
  line `six months aforesaid to the date on which the refund is granted.`
  line `3 [( 3A ) Where the whole or any part of the refund referred it in sub-section ( 3 ) is due to an`
  line `assessee as a result of any amount having been paid by him after the 31st day of March, 1975, in`
  line `pursuance of any order of assessment or penalty and such amount or any part thereof having been`
  line `found in appeal or other proceeding under this Act to be in excess of the amount which such assessee`
  line `is liable to pay as tax or penalty, as the case may be, under this Act, the Central Government shall`
  line `pay to such assessee simple interest at the rate specified in sub-section ( 3 ) on the amount so found to`
  line `be in excess from the date on which such amount was paid to the date on which the refund is`
  line `granted:`
  line `Provided that, where the amount so found to be in excess was paid in instalments, such interest`
  line `shall be payable on the amount of each such instalments or any part of such instalment, which was in`
  line `excess, from the date on which such instalment was paid to the date on which the refund is granted:`
  line `Provided further that no interest under this sub-section shall be payable for a period of one month`
  line `from the date of the passing of the order in appeal or other proceeding:`
  line `Provided also that, where any interest is payable to an assessee under this sub-section, no interest`
  line `under sub-section ( 3 ) shall be payable to him in respect of the amount so found to be in excess.]`
  line `( 4 ) Where a refund is withheld under the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ), the Central Government`
  line `shall pay interest at the aforesaid rate on the amount of refund ultimately determined to be due as a`
  line `result of the appeal or further proceedings for a period commencing after the expiry of six months`
  line `from the date of the order referred to in that sub-section to the date the refund is granted.`
  line `4 [( 4A ) The provisions of sub-sections ( 3 ), ( 3A ) and ( 4 ) shall not apply in respect of any`
  line `assessment for the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1989, or any subsequent`
  line `assessment year.`
  line `( 4B ) ( a ) 5 [Where refund of any amount becomes due to the assessee under this Act,] he shall,`
  line `subject to the provisions of this sub-section, be entitled to receive, in addition to the said amount,`
  line `simple interest thereon calculated at the rate of one 6 * * * per cent. for every month or part of a`
  line `month comprised in the period or periods from the date or, as the case may be, dates of payment of`
  line `the tax or penalty to the date on which the refund is granted.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this clause, “date of payment of the tax or penalty” means the`
  line `date on and from which the amount of tax or penalty specified in the notice of demand issued under`
  line `section 31 is paid in excess of such demand.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Gift - tax Officer” ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 75, for “twelve per cent. ” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1984).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 118 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 180 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 90, for “Where, in pursu ance of any order passed under this Act, the refund of any amount`
  line `becomes due to the assess” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `6. The words “and a half” omitted by Act 49 of 1991, s. 89 (w.e.f. 1 -10-1991).`
