obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line 43
  line `( b ) If the proceedings resulting in the refund are delayed for reasons attributable to the assessee,`
  line `whether wholly or in part, period of the delay so attributable to him shall be excluded from the period`
  line `for which interest is payable, and where any question arises as to the period to be excluded, it shall be`
  line `decided by the Chief Commissioner or Commissioner whose decision thereon shall be final.`
  line `( c ) Where, as a result of an order under 1 [sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 5 ) of section 15 or]`
  line `section 16 or section 22 or section 23 or section 24 or section 26 or section 28 or section 34, the`
  line `amount on which the interest was payable under clause ( a ) has been increased or reduced, as the case`
  line `may be, interest shall be increased or reduced accordingly, and, in a case where the interest is`
  line `reduced, the Assessing Officer shall serve on the assessee a notice of demand in the prescribed form`
  line `specifying the amount of the excess interest paid and requiring him to pay such amount; and such`
  line `notice of demand shall be deemed to be a notice under section 31 and the provisions of this Act shall`
  line `apply accordingly.`
  line `( d ) The provisions of this sub-section shall apply in respect of assessments for the assessment`
  line `year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1989, and subsequent assessment years.]`
  line `( 5 ) Where under any of the provisions of this Act, a refund is found to be due to any person, the`
  line `2 [Assessing Officer], 3 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 4 [Commissioner (Appeals)] or 5 [Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner], as the case may be, may, in lieu of payment of the refund, set off the`
  line `amount to be refunded or any part of that amount, against the sum, if any, remaining payable under this`
  line `Act by the person to whom the refund is due, after giving an intimation in writing to such person of the`
  line `action proposed to be taken under this section.]`
  line `CHAPTER VIII`
  line `M ISCELLANEOUS`
  line `6 [ 34. Rectification of mistakes. — ( 1 ) With a view to rectifying any mistake apparent from the`
  line `record —`
  line `( a ) the 2 [Assessing Officer] may amend any order of assessment or of refund or any other order`
  line `passed by him;`
  line `7 [( aa ) a gift-tax authority may amend any intimation sent by it under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 15`
  line `or enhance or reduce the amount of refund granted by it under that sub-section;]`
  line `8 [( b ) the 9 [Joint Director] or 10 [Joint Commissioner] or Director or Commissioner or Deputy`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals) or Commissioner (Appeals) may amend any order passed by him under`
  line `section 17A;`
  line `( c ) the Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or Commissioner (Appeals) may amend any order`
  line `passed by him under section 22 11 * * *;`
  line `( d ) the Commissioner may amend any order passed by him under section 24;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 90 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by A ct 4 of 1988, s. 161 for “Gift - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 161, ibid., for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 1 61, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 26, for section 34 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 181 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 186, ibid., for “clauses ( b ), ( c ), ( d ) and ( e )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 76, for “Deputy Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `10. Subs. by s. 76, ibid., for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `11. The words, figures and letter “or section 22A” omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 91 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
