obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line 44
  line `( e ) the Appellate Tribunal may amend any order passed by it under section 23 or section 25.]`
  line `( 2 ) Subject to the other provisions of this section, the authority concerned —`
  line `( a ) may make an amendment under sub-section ( 1 ) of its own motion; and`
  line `( b ) shall make such amendment for rectifying any such mistake which has been brought to its`
  line `notice by the assessee, and where the authority concerned is the 1 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)]`
  line `2 [or the Commissioner (Appeals)] or the Appellate Tribunal, by the 3 [Assessing Officer] also.`
  line `( 3 ) An amendment, which has the effect of enhancing an assessment or reducing a refund or`
  line `otherwise increasing the liability of the assessee, shall not be made under this section unless the authority`
  line `concerned has given notice to the assessee of its intention so to do and has allowed the assessee a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line `( 4 ) Where an amendment is made under this section, an order shall be passed in writing by the`
  line `gift-tax authority concerned.`
  line `( 5 ) Subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) of 4 [section 33A], where any such amendment has the`
  line `effect of reducing the assessment, the 3 [Assessing Officer] shall make any refund which may be due to`
  line `such assessee.`
  line `( 6 ) Where any such amendment has the effect of enhancing the assessment or reducing a refund`
  line `already made, the 3 [Assessing Officer] shall serve on the assessee a notice of demand in the prescribed`
  line `form specifying the sum payable, and such notice of demand shall be deemed to be issued under`
  line `section 31 and the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly.`
  line `( 7 ) No amendment under this section shall be made after the expiry of four years 5 [from the end of the`
  line `financial year in which the order sought to be amended was passed].]`
  line `35. Prosecution. — ( 1 ) If any person fails without reasonable cause, —`
  line `( a ) to furnish in due time any return of gifts under this Act;`
  line `( b ) to produce, or cause to be produced, on or before the date mentioned in any notice under`
  line `6 * * * sub-section ( 4 ) of section 15, such accounts, records and documents as are referred to in the`
  line notice;
  line `7 * * * * *`
  line `he shall, on conviction before a magistrate, be punishable with fine which may extend to rupees ten for`
  line `every day during which the default continues.`
  line `( 2 ) If a person makes a statement in a verification in any return of gift furnished under this Act or in a`
  line `verification mentioned in section 22, 23 or 25 which is false, and which he either knows or believes to be`
  line `false, or does not believe to be true, he shall, on conviction before a magistrate, be punishable with simple`
  line `imprisonment which may extend to one year, or with fine which may extend to rupees one thousand, or`
  line `with both.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Gift - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 5 of 1 964, s. 52, for “section 33” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1963).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 76, for “from the date of the order sought to be amended” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1984).`
  line `6. The words, brackets and figure “sub -section ( 2 )” omitted by Act 41 of 1975, s. 119 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `7. Clause ( c ) omitted by s. 119. ibid, (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
