obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line 45
  line `1 [( 2A ) If a person abets or induces in any manner another person to make and deliver an account,`
  line `statement or declaration relating to any gifts chargeable to tax which is false and which he either knows to`
  line `be false or does not believe to be true, he shall, on conviction before a magistrate, be punishable with`
  line `simple imprisonment which may extend to six months or with fine which may extend to one thousand`
  line `rupees, or with both.]`
  line `2 [( 3 ) A person shall not be proceeded against for an offence under this Act except with the previous`
  line `sanction of the Commissioner or Commissioner (Appeals):`
  line `Provided that the Chief Commissioner or, as the case may be, Director General may issue such`
  line `instructions or directions to the aforesaid gift-tax authorities as he may deem fit for institution of`
  line `proceedings under this sub-section.`
  line `( 4 ) Any such offence may, either before or after the institution or proceedings, be compounded by the`
  line `Chief Commissioner or Director General.]`
  line `3 [ 4 [ Explanation 1 ]. —For the purposes of this section, “magistrate” means a presidency magistrate or`
  line `a magistrate of the first class.]`
  line `5 [ Explanation 2. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the power of the Board to`
  line `issue orders, instructions or directions under this Act shall include and shall be deemed always to have`
  line `included the power to issue instructions or directions (including instructions or directions to obtain the`
  line `previous approval of the Board) to other gift-tax authorities for the proper composition of offences under`
  line `this section.]`
  line `6 [35A. Offences by companies. — ( 1 ) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), where an offence under this Act, has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “company” means a body corporate, and includes—`
  line `( i ) a firm, and`
  line `( ii ) an association of persons or a body of individuals, whether incorporated or not; and`
  line `( b ) “director”, in relation to—`
  line `( i ) a firm, means a partner in the firm,`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 90, for sub-sections ( 3 ) and ( 4 ) (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 27, for Explanation (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `4. The Explanation renumbered as Explanation 1 thereof by Act 49 of 1991, s. 90 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 90, ibid, (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1958.)`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 120 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
