  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  sourcePage 46
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line 46
  line `( ii ) an association of persons or a body of individuals means any member controlling the affairs`
  line thereof.
  line `35B. Offences by Hindu undivided families. — ( 1 ) Where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a Hindu undivided family, the karta thereof shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and`
  line `shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render the karta liable to any punishment if`
  line `he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised all due`
  line `diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a Hindu undivided family and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the`
  line `consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any member of the Hindu`
  line `undivided family, such member shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be`
  line `proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line `35C. Section 360 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 and the Probation of Offenders`
  line `Act, 1958, not to apply. — Nothing contained in section 360 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2`
  line `of 1974), or in the Probation of Offenders Act, 1958 (20 of 1958), shall apply to a person convicted of an`
  line `offence under this Act unless that person is under eighteen years of age.]`
  line `1 [ 35D. Presumption as to culpable mental state. — ( 1 ) In any prosecution for any offence under this`
  line `Act which requires a culpable mental state on the part of the accused, the court shall presume the`
  line `existence of such mental state but it shall be a defence for the accused to prove the fact that he had no`
  line `such mental state with respect to the act charged as an offence in that prosecution.`
  line `Explanation. — In this sub- section, “culpable mental state” includes intention, motive or knowledge of`
  line `a fact, or belief in or reason to believe, a fact.`
  line `( 2 ) For the purposes of this section, a fact is said to be proved only when the court believes it to exist`
  line `beyond reasonable doubt and not merely when its existence is established by a preponderance of`
  line probability.]
  line `2 [35E. Proof of entries in records or documents. — Entries in the records or other documents in the`
  line `custody of a gift-tax authority shall be admitted in evidence in any proceedings for the prosecution of any`
  line `person for an offence under this Act, and all such entries may be proved either by the production of the`
  line `records or other documents in the custody of the gift-tax authority containing such entries, or by the`
  line `production of a copy of the entries certified by the gift-tax authority having custody of the records or`
  line `other documents under its signature and stating that it is a true copy of the original entries and that such`
  line `original entries are contained in the records or other documents in its custody.]`
  line `3 [ 36. Power regarding discovery, production of evidence, etc. — ( 1 ) The 4 [Assessing Officer], the`
  line `5 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 6 [the Commissioner (Appeals)], the 7 [Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner] and the Appellate Tribunal shall, for the purposes of this Act, have the same powers as`
  line `are vested in a court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), when trying a suit in respect of`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 41 (w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 92 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 28, for section 36 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Gift - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 161, ibid., for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
