obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line 47
  line `the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) discovery and inspection;`
  line `( b ) enforcing the attendance of any person, including any officer of a banking company and`
  line `examining him on oath;`
  line `( c ) compelling the production of books of account and other documents; and`
  line `( d ) issuing commissions.`
  line `1 [( 1A ) If the Director General or Director or 2 [Joint Director] or 3 [Assistant Director or Deputy`
  line `Director] has reason to suspect that any gifts chargeable to tax under this Act have been concealed, or are`
  line `likely to be concealed, by any person or class of persons within his jurisdiction, then, for the purposes of`
  line `making any inquiry or investigation relating thereto, it shall be competent for him to exercise the powers`
  line `conferred under sub-section ( 1 ) on the gift-tax authorities referred to in that sub-section, notwithstanding`
  line `that no proceedings with respect to such person or class of persons are pending before him or any other`
  line `gift-tax authority.]`
  line `4 * * * * *]`
  line `37. Power to call for information. — 5 [ Where, for the purposes of this Act, it appears necessary for`
  line `any gift-tax authority to obtain any statement or information from any person or banking company,]`
  line `6 [such gift-tax authority] may serve a notice requiring such person, on or before a date to be therein`
  line `specified, to furnish such statement or information on the points specified in the notice, and that person`
  line `shall, notwithstanding anything in any law to the contrary, be bound to furnish such statement or`
  line `information to 6 [such gift-tax authority]:`
  line `Provided that no legal practitioner shall be bound to furnish any statement or information under this`
  line `section based on any professional communications made to him otherwise than as permitted by section`
  line `126 of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872).`
  line `38. Effect of transfer of authorities on pending proceedings. — Whenever in respect of any`
  line `proceeding under this Act any gift-tax authority ceases to exercise jurisdiction and is succeeded by`
  line `another who has and exercises such jurisdiction, the authority so succeeding may continue the proceeding`
  line `from the stage at which the proceeding was left by his predecessor:`
  line `7 [Provided that the assessee concerned may demand that before the proceeding is so continued the`
  line `previous proceeding or any part thereof be reopened or that before any order of assessment is passed`
  line `against him, he be reheard.]`
  line `8 [ 39. Computation of period of limitation. — In computing the period of limitation prescribed for`
  line `an appeal or an application under this Act, the day on which the order complained of was served and if`
  line `the assessee was not furnished with a copy of the order when the notice of the order was served upon him,`
  line `the time requisite for obtaining a copy of such order shall be excluded.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 70 (w.e.f. 1-6-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 76, for “Deputy Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 76, ibid., for “Assistant Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `4. Sub-section ( 2 ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 182 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 183, ibid., for “Where, for the purposes of determining the gift -tax payable by any person, it appears necessary for`
  line `the Gift- tax Officer to obtain any statement or information from any person” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 183, ibid., for “the Gift - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `7. The Proviso added by Act 53 of 1962, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 30, ibid., for section 39 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
