obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line 48
  line `40. Service of notice. — ( 1 ) A notice or a requisition under this Act may be served on the person`
  line `therein named either by post or as if it were a summons issued by a court under the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
  line `( 2 ) Any such notice or requisition may, in the case of a firm or a Hindu undivided family, be`
  line `addressed to any member of the firm or to the manager or any adult male member of the family, and in`
  line `the case of a company or association of persons be addressed to the principal officer thereof.`
  line `1 [( 3 ) After a finding of total partition has been recorded by the 2 [Assessing Officer] under section 20`
  line `in respect of any Hindu family, notices under this Act in respect of the gifts made by the family, shall be`
  line `served on the person who was the last manager of the Hindu family, or if such person is dead, then on all`
  line `surviving adults who were members of the Hindu family immediately before the partition.`
  line `( 4 ) Where a firm or other association of persons is dissolved, notices under this Act in respect of the`
  line `gifts made by the firm or association may be served on any person who was a partner (not being a minor)`
  line `or member of the association, as the case may be, immediately before its dissolution.]`
  line `[ 41. Prohibition of disclosure of information. ] — Omitted by the Finance Act, 1964 (5 of 1964),`
  line `s. 52 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1964). Earlier, this section was substituted by the Gift-tax (Amendment) Act, 1962 (53 of`
  line `1962), s. 32 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `3 [ 41A. Publication of information respecting assessees. — ( 1 ) If the Central Government is of`
  line `opinion that it is necessary or expedient in the public interest to publish the names of any assessees and`
  line `any other particulars relating to any proceedings 4 [or prosecutions] under this Act in respect of such`
  line `assessees, it may cause to be published such names and particulars in such manner as it thinks fit.`
  line `5 [( 2 ) No publication under this section shall be made in relation to any penalty imposed under this Act`
  line `until the time for presenting an appeal to the 6 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 7 [or, as the case may be,`
  line `the Commissioner (Appeals)] has expired without an appeal having been presented or the appeal, if`
  line `presented, has been disposed of.]`
  line `Explanation. — In the case of a firm, company or other association of persons, the names of the`
  line `partners of the firm, directors, managing agents, secretaries and treasurers or managers of the company, or`
  line `the members of the association, as the case may be, may also be published if, in the opinion of the Central`
  line `Government, the circumstances of the case justify it.`
  line `41B. Disclosure of information respecting assessees. — Where a person makes an application to`
  line `the 8 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner] in the prescribed form for any information relating to any`
  line `assessee in respect of any assessment made under this Act, the 8 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner]`
  line `may, if he is satisfied that it is in the public interest so to do, furnish or cause to be furnished the`
  line `information asked for in respect of that assessment only and his decision in this behalf shall be final and`
  line `shall not be called in question in any court of law.]`
  line `9 [ 41C. Return of gifts, etc., not to be invalid on certain grounds. — No return of gifts,`
  line `assessment, notice, summons or other proceeding, furnished or made or issued or taken or purported to`
  line `have been furnished or made or issued or taken in pursuance of any of the provisions of this Act shall be`
  line `invalid or shall be deemed to be invalid merely by reason of any mistake, defect or omission in such`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Gift - tax Officer” (w.e. f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 5 of 1964, s. 52, for sections 41A and 41B (w.e.f. 1-4-1964).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 121 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 121, ibid., for sub-section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 122 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
