obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line 49
  line `return of gifts, assessment, notice summons or other proceeding, if such return of gifts, assessment, notice`
  line `summons or other proceeding is in substance and effect in conformity with or according to the intent and`
  line `purpose of this Act.]`
  line `42. Bar of suits in civil court. — No suit shall lie in any civil court to set aside or modify`
  line `1 [any proceeding taken or order made] under this Act, and no prosecution, suit or other legal proceedings`
  line `shall lie against 2 [the Government or] any officer of the Government for anything in good faith done or`
  line `intended to be done under this Act.`
  line `3 [ 43. Appearance before gift-tax authorities by authorised representatives. — An assessee who is`
  line `entitled to or required to attend before any gift-tax authority or the Appellate Tribunal in connection with`
  line `any proceeding under this Act, except where he is required under this Act to attend in person, may attend`
  line `by a person who would be entitled to represent him before any income-tax authority or the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal under section 288 of the Income-tax Act.]`
  line `4 [ 43A. Appearance by registered valuer in certain matters. — Any assessee who is entitled or`
  line `required to attend before any gift-tax authority or the Appellate Tribunal in connection with any matter`
  line `relating to the valuation of any asset, except where he is required under this Act to attend in person, may`
  line `attend by a registered valuer.`
  line `Explanation. —In this section, “registered valuer” has the same meaning as in clause ( oaa ) of`
  line `section 2 of the Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957).]`
  line `44. Agreement for avoidance or relief of double taxation with respect to gift-tax. — 5 [The`
  line `Central Government may enter into an agreement with the Government of any reciprocating country —`
  line `( a ) for the avoidance or relief of double taxation with respect to gift-tax payable under this Act`
  line `and under the corresponding law in force in the reciprocating country, or`
  line `( b ) for exchange of information for the prevention of evasion or avoidance of gift-tax chargeable`
  line `under this Act or under the corresponding law in force in that country or investigation of cases of`
  line `such evasion or avoidance, or`
  line `( c ) for recovery of tax under this Act and under the corresponding law in force in that country,`
  line `and may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make such provision as may be necessary for`
  line `implementing the agreement.]`
  line `Explanation. —The expression “reciprocating country” for the purposes o f this Act means any country`
  line `which the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare to be a reciprocating`
  line country.
  line `6 [ 44A. Rounding off of taxable gifts. — The amount assessed in accordance with the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Act as being the value of all taxable gifts shall be rounded off to the nearest multiple of`
  line `ten rupees and, for this purpose, any part of a rupee consisting of paise shall be ignored and thereafter, if`
  line `such amount is not a multiple of ten rupees, then, if the last figure in that amount is five or more, the`
  line `amount shall be increased to the next higher amount which is a multiple of ten and, if the last figure is less`
  line `than five, the amount shall be reduced to the next lower amount which is a multiple of ten; and the`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 71, for “any order made” (w.e.f. 1 -3-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 5 of 1964, s. 52 (w.e.f. 1-4-1964).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 34, for section 43 (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 45 of 1972, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-1-1973).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 54, for the portion beginning with words “The Central Government may” and ending with the`
  line `words “for implementing the agreement.” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1972).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 70 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
