obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line 50
  line `amount so rounded off shall be deemed to be the value of all taxable gifts of the assessee for the purposes`
  line `of this Act.`
  line `44B. Rounding off of tax, etc. — The amount of gift-tax, interest, penalty, fine or any other sum`
  line `payable, and the amount of refund due, under the provisions of this Act, shall be rounded off to the`
  line `nearest rupee and, for this purpose, where such amount contains a part of a rupee consisting of paise, then,`
  line `if such part is fifty paise or more, it shall be increased to one rupee, and if such part is less than fifty paise,`
  line `it shall be ignored.]`
  line `45. Act not to apply in certain cases. — 1 [No tax shall be levied under this Act in respect of gifts`
  line `made by] —`
  line `2 [( a ) a company in which the public are substantially interested;`
  line `( b ) any company to an Indian company in a scheme of amalgamation;]`
  line `3 [( e ) any institution or fund the income whereof is exempt from income-tax under`
  line `4 [section 11 or section 12] of the Income-tax Act.]`
  line `5 [ Explanation 1. — For the purposes of clause ( b ), the term “amalgamation” shall have the meaning`
  line `assigned to it in clause ( 1B ) of section 2 of the Income-tax Act.]`
  line `6 [ Explanation 3. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the exemption admissible`
  line `under clause ( e ) in relation to gifts made by an institution or fund referred to in that clause shall not be`
  line `denied merely on either or both of the following grounds, namely: —`
  line `( i ) that, subsequent to the gift, any part of the income of the institution or fund has become`
  line `chargeable to tax due to non-compliance with any of the provisions of 7 [section 11 or section 12 or`
  line `section 12A] of the Income-tax Act;`
  line `( ii ) that, under clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 13 of the Income-tax Act, the exemption`
  line `under 8 [section 11 or section 12] of that Act is denied to the institution or fund in relation to any`
  line `income arising to it from any investment referred to in clause ( h ) of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 13 of`
  line `the said Act where the aggregate of the funds invested by it in a concern referred to in the said`
  line `clause ( h ) does not exceed five per cent. of the capital of that concern.]`
  line `46. Power to make rules. — ( 1 ) The Board may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules`
  line `for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, rules made under this`
  line `section may provide for —`
  line `( a ) the manner in which the value of any property may be determined;`
  line `( b ) the form in which returns under this Act shall be made and the manner in which they shall be`
  line verified;
  line `( c ) the form in which appeals and applications under this Act may be made, and the manner in`
  line `which they shall be verified;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 184, for “The provisions of this Act shall not apply to gifts made by” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 184, ibid., for clause ( a ), ( b ), ( c ), ( d ) and ( da ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 184, ibid., for clause ( e ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 55, for “section 11” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1973).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 93, for Explanations 1 and 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 32 of 1971, s. 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 55, for “section 11” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1973).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 55, for “section 11” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1973).`
