obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line 51
  line `1 [( cc ) the circumstances in which, the conditions subject to which and the manner in which, the`
  line `2 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 3 [or the Commissioner (Appeals)] may permit an appellant to`
  line `produce evidence which he did not produce or which he was not allowed to produce before the`
  line `4 [Assessing Officer];`
  line `( d ) the form of any notice of demand under this Act;`
  line `( e ) the refunds of gift-tax paid in respect of gifts which are revoked on the happening of any`
  line `specified event which does not depend on the will of the donor or of any amount paid under section`
  line 18;
  line `5 [( ee ) the procedure to be followed in calculating interest payable by assessees or interest`
  line `payable by the Government to assessees under any provisions of this Act, including the rounding off`
  line `of the period for which such interest is to be calculated in cases where such period includes a fraction`
  line `of a month, and specifying the circumstances in which and the extent to which petty amounts of`
  line `interest payable by assessees may be ignored;]`
  line `( f ) the areas for which lists of valuers may be drawn up;`
  line `( g ) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed for the purposes of this Act.`
  line `6 [( 3 ) The power to make rules conferred by this section shall include the power to give retrospective`
  line `effect, from a date not earlier than the date of commencement of this Act, to the rules or any of them and,`
  line `unless the contrary is permitted (whether expressly or by necessary implication), no retrospective effect`
  line `shall be given to any rule so as to prejudicially affect the interests of assessees.]`
  line `7 [( 4 ) The Central Government shall cause every rule made under this Act to be laid as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session 8 [or in two or more successive sessions], and if, before the expiry`
  line `of the session 9 [immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid] both Houses agree`
  line `in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule`
  line `shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be, so however,`
  line `that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously`
  line `done under that rule.]`
  line `10 [ 46A. Power to make exemption, etc., in relation to certain Union territories. — ( 1 ) If the`
  line `Central Government considers it necessary or expedient so to do for avoiding any hardship or anomaly or`
  line `removing any difficulty that may arise as a result of the application of this Act to the Union territories of`
  line `Dadra and Nagar Haveli, Goa, Daman and Diu and Pondicherry, or in the case of the Union territory of`
  line `Pondicherry, for implementing any provision of the Treaty of Cession concluded between France and`
  line `India on the 28th day of May, 1956, the Central Government may, by general or special order, make an`
  line `exemption, reduction in rate or other modification in respect of gift-tax in favour of any class of gifts or in`
  line `regard to the whole or any part of the gifts made by any assessee or class of assessees:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 56, (w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for "Appellate Assistant Commissioner" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 161, for “Gift - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 71 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 26 of 1974, s. 19, for sub-section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 18-8-1974).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 53 of 1962, s. 36, for “sub -section ( 4 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 123, for “or in two successive sessions” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1976).`
  line `9. Subs. by s. 123, ibid., for “in which it is so laid or the session immediately following” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1976).`
  line `10. Ins. by The Taxation Laws (Extension to Union Territories) Regulation, 1963 (3 of 1963), by s. 3 and the Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
