obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line 54
  line `1 [SCHEDULE II`
  line `[ See section 6( 1 )]`
  line `R ULES FOR DETERMINING THE VALUE OF PROPERTY GIFTED`
  line `1. Value of gifted property, how to be determined. — 2 [Subject to the provisions of rules 2 to 7, the`
  line `value of any property], other than cash, transferred by way of gift shall, for the purposes of this Act, be`
  line `determined in accordance with the provisions of Schedule III to 3 [the Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957)`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as the Wealth-tax Act)], which shall apply subject to the following modifications,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `In the said Schedule, —`
  line `( a ) references by whatever form of words to the Wealth-tax Act shall be construed as references`
  line `to this Act;`
  line `( b ) in rule 5, the reference to the year ending on the valuation date shall be construed as a`
  line `reference to the previous year as defined in this Act;`
  line `( c ) save as provided in clause ( b ), references to the valuation date shall be construed as`
  line `references to the date on which the gift was made;`
  line `( d ) reference to section 7 of the Wealth-tax Act shall be construed as references to section 6 of`
  line `this Act;`
  line `( e ) references to section 16A of the Wealth-tax Act shall be construed as references to`
  line `sub-section (6) of section 15 of this Act.]`
  line `4 [ 2. Quoted shares and debentures of companies. — The value of an equity share or a preference`
  line `share in any company or a debenture of any company which is a quoted share or a quoted debenture shall`
  line `be taken as the value quoted in respect of such share or debenture on the date on which the gift was made`
  line `or where there is no such quotation on such date, the quotation on the date closest to such date and`
  line `immediately preceding such date.`
  line `Explanation. — The words and expressions used in this rule and rules 3 to 7 but not defined and`
  line `defined in rule 2 of Schedule III to the Wealth-tax Act shall have the meanings respectively assigned to`
  line `them in rule 2 of that Schedule.`
  line `3. Special provision for quoted shares of companies. — Notwithstanding anything in rule 2, the`
  line `value of an equity share in any company which is a quoted share may, at the option of the assessee or a`
  line `company, be taken on the basis of the average of the value quoted on the 31st day of March immediately`
  line `preceding the assessment year and the values quoted in respect of such share on the said dates in relation`
  line `to each of the immediately preceding nine assessment years, or where there is no such quotation on any of`
  line `the aforesaid dates, the quotation on the date closest to the said date and immediately preceding such`
  line `date:`
  line `Provided that where for any reason the value of such share is quoted in relation to lesser number of`
  line `assessment years than the said nine assessment years, then the value or values so quoted shall be taken`
  line `into account for the purposes of the aforesaid average:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 94 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Ac t 38 of 1993, s. 42, for “The value of property” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1993).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 42, ibid., for “the Wealth - tax Act” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1993).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 42, ibid, (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
