obj_root_law_sections_55:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-55
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Page 55`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  sourcePage 55
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line 55
  line `Provided further that where the assessee opts for the average of the values so quoted, he shall get such`
  line `values certified by an accountant and attach the certificate to the return of gifts in respect of the relevant`
  line `assessment year.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this rule, “accountant” shall have the same meaning as in`
  line `the Explanation below sub-section ( 2 ) of section 288 of the Income-tax Act.`
  line `4. Unquoted preference shares. — ( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of sub-rule ( 2 ), the value of an`
  line `unquoted preference share in any company shall, —`
  line `( a ) where the preference share is issued before the date on which the gift was made at a rate of`
  line `dividend of not less than eight per cent. be the paid-up value of such share; and`
  line `( b ) where the preference share is issued before the said date at a rate of dividend of less than`
  line `eight per cent. be the adjusted paid-up value of such share.`
  line `( 2 ) Where no dividend has been paid in respect of an unquoted preference share by any company`
  line `continuously for not less than three accounting years ending on the date on which the gift was made or, in`
  line `a case where the accounting year of the company does not end on that date, for not less than three`
  line `continuous accounting years ending on a date immediately before the date on which the gift was made,`
  line `the paid-up value or, as the case may be, the adjusted paid-up value shall be reduced —`
  line `( a ) in the case of a non-cumulative preference share, as indicated in the Table below:`
  line TABLE
  line `Number of accounting years ending on the date on which the gift`
  line `was made or, in a case where the accounting year does not end`
  line `on that date, the number of accounting years ending on a date`
  line `immediately preceding the date on which the gift was made, for`
  line `which no dividend has been paid`
  line `Rate of reduction`
  line `( 1 ) ( 2 )`
  line `Three Years 10%`
  line `of the paid-up value or`
  line `the adjusted paid-up`
  line `value, as the case may`
  line be;
  line `Four Years 20%`
  line `Five Years 30%`
  line `Six Years and above 40%`
  line `( b ) in the case of a cumulative preference share, by one-half of the rates specified in the aforesaid`
  line Table.
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this rule, “adjusted paid - up value”, in relation to a preference`
  line `share, means an amount which bears to the paid-up value of the preference share the same proportion`
  line `as the stipulated rate of dividend [being the rate of dividend on the preference share specified in the`
  line `terms of issue of such share, and in a case where such dividend is required to be increased under the`
  line `provisions of section 3 of the Preference Shares (Regulation of Dividends) Act, 1960 (63 of 1960),`
  line `the rate of dividend as so increased] on such share bears to the rate of eight per cent.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-56
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Page 56`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  sourcePage 56
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line 56
  line `5. Unquoted equity shares in companies other than investment companies. — ( 1 ) The value of an`
  line `unquoted equity share in any company, other than an investment company, shall be determined in the`
  line `manner set out in sub-rule ( 2 ).`
  line `( 2 ) The value of all the liabilities as shown in the balance sheet of such company shall be deducted`
  line `from the value of all its assets shown in that balance sheet; the net amount so arrived at shall be divided`
  line `by the total amount of its paid-up equity share capital as shown in the balance sheet; the result multiplied`
  line `by the paid-up value of each equity share shall be in the break-up value of each unquoted equity share,`
  line `and an amount equal to eighty per cent. of the break-up value so determined shall be the value of the`
  line `unquoted equity share for the purposes of this Act.`
  line `( 3 ) For the purposes of sub-rule ( 2 ), —`
  line `( a ) the following amounts shown as assets in the balance sheet shall not be treated as assets,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( i ) any amount paid as advance tax under the Income-tax Act;`
  line `( ii ) any amount shown in the balance sheet including the debit balance of the profit and loss`
  line `account or the profit and loss appropriation account which does not represent the value of any`
  line asset;
  line `( b ) the following amounts shown as liabilities in the balance sheet shall not be treated as`
  line `liabilities, namely: —`
  line `( i ) the paid-up capital in respect of equity shares;`
  line `( ii ) the amount set apart for payment of dividends on preference shares and equity shares`
  line `where such dividends have not been declared before the date on which the gift was made at a`
  line `general body meeting of the company;`
  line `( iii ) reserves, by whatever name called, other than those set apart towards depreciation;`
  line `( iv ) credit balance of the profit and loss account;`
  line `( v ) any amount representing provision for taxation, other than the amount referred to in`
  line `sub-clause ( i ) of clause ( a ), to the extent of the excess over the tax payable with reference to the`
  line `book profits in accordance with the law applicable thereto;`
  line `( vi ) any amount representing contingent liabilities other than arrears of dividends payable in`
  line `respect of cumulative preference shares.`
  line `Explanation. —For the purposes of this rule, “balance sheet”, in relation to any company, means the`
  line `balance sheet of such company (including the Notes annexed thereto and forming part of the accounts) as`
  line `drawn up on the date on which the gift was made and, where there is no such balance sheet, the balance`
  line `sheet drawn up on a date immediately preceding that date, and, in the absence of both, the balance sheet`
  line `drawn up on a date immediately after the date on which the gift was made.`
  line `6. Unquoted equity shares in investment companies. ( 1 ) Subject to rule 7, the value of an unquoted`
  line `equity share in an investment company shall be determined in the manner specified in sub-rule ( 2 ).`
  line `( 2 ) The value of all the liabilities as shown in the balance sheet of such company shall be deducted`
  line `from the value of all its assets shown in that balance sheet; the net amount so arrived at shall be divided`
  line `by the total paid-up equity share capital of the company as shown in the balance sheet, and the result`
  line `multiplied by the paid-up value of each equity share shall be the value of the unquoted equity share in that`
  line `investment company for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-57
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Page 57`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  sourcePage 57
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line 57
  line `( 3 ) For the purposes of sub-rule ( 2 ), the value of an asset disclosed in the balance sheet of the`
  line `company shall be taken to be its value determined in accordance with the rules as applicable to that`
  line `particular asset and, in the absence of any such rule, the value of such asset shall be its value as`
  line `determined under rule 20 of Schedule III to the Wealth-tax Act.`
  line `( 4 ) For the purposes of this rule, —`
  line `( a ) “balance sheet” has the same meaning as in rule 5;`
  line `( b ) the amounts referred to in sub-rule ( 3 ) of rule 5 shall not be treated as assets or liabilities.`
  line `( 5 ) For the purpose of facilitating the valuation of unquoted equity shares under this rule and rule 7,`
  line `the company concerned shall have such valuation made by its auditors appointed under section 224 of the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), and a certificate of the auditors relating to such valuation in the`
  line `prescribed form shall be furnished to the Assessing Officer and the shareholders of the company; and the`
  line `valuation made by the auditors shall be taken into account in the assessment of the shareholders of the`
  line company.
  line `7. Unquoted equity shares in interlocked companies. — ( 1 ) The value of an unquoted equity share`
  line `in one of the two interlocked companies held by the other interlocked company for the purposes of rule 6`
  line `shall be equal to the paid-up value of such share or the value determined under sub-rule ( 2 ), whichever is`
  line higher.
  line `( 2 ) For the purpose of sub-rule ( 1 ), the aggregate value of all the equity shares in an interlocked`
  line `company shall be arrived at by multiplying the maintainable profits of such company by —`
  line `( a ) the fraction 100/8.5, in a case where the gross total income of the company consists, to the`
  line `extent of not less than 51 per cent. of income chargeable under the head “Income from house`
  line `property” under the Incom e-tax Act; or`
  line `( b ) the fraction 100/10, in the case of any other interlocked company,`
  line `and the resultant amount divided by the number of such equity shares shall be the value of such an equity`
  line `share in such company.`
  line `( 3 ) The maintainable profits of the company, for the purpose of sub-rule ( 2 ), shall be computed in the`
  line `following manner, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the book profits of the company for the five accounting years of the company immediately`
  line `preceding the date on which the gift was made shall first be ascertained;`
  line `( b ) adjustments shall be made to the book profits for each of the said five years for all non-`
  line `recurring and extraordinary items of income and expenditure and losses;`
  line `( c ) adjustments shall be made to the book profits for expenditure which is not of a revenue nature`
  line `but is debited in the accounts and for receipts which are in the nature of revenue receipts but are not`
  line `accounted for in the profit and loss account;`
  line `( d ) any development rebate or investment allowance debited in the books of account shall be`
  line `added back to the book profits;`
  line `( e ) the tax liability of the company on the book profits, arrived at after the adjustments at`
  line `items ( a ), ( b ), ( c ) and ( d ), shall be deducted from such book profits;`
  line `( f ) amounts required for paying dividends on preference share or shares with prior rights shall be`
  line `deducted from such book profits;`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-58
